  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Multiplies in Egypt'
      title: Israel Multiplies in Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the names of the sons of Israel who came to Egypt
        with Jacob; each came with his household: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Dan and Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All the descendants of Jacob were seventy people; Joseph was [already]
        in Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Joseph died, and all his brothers and all that generation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but the Israelites were prolific and increased greatly; they multiplied
        and became extremely strong, so that the land was filled with them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Now a new king arose over Egypt, who did not know Joseph [nor the
        history of his accomplishments]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He said to his people, \u201CBehold, the people of the sons of Israel
        are too many and too mighty for us [they greatly outnumber us]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Come, let us deal shrewdly with them, so that they will not multiply
        and in the event of war, join our enemies, and fight against us and escape
        from the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So they set taskmasters over them to oppress them with hard labor.
        And the sons of Israel built Pithom and Raamses as storage cities for Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the more the Egyptians oppressed them, the more they multiplied
        and expanded, so that the Egyptians dreaded and were exasperated by the Israelites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the Egyptians made the Israelites serve rigorously [forcing them
        into severe slavery]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They made their lives bitter with hard labor in mortar, brick, and
        all kinds of field work. All their labor was harsh and severe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the king of Egypt said to the Hebrew midwives, one of whom was
        named Shiphrah (beauty) and the other named Puah (splendor), '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWhen you act as midwives to the Hebrew women and see them on
        the birthstool, if it is a son, you shall kill him; but if it is a daughter,
        she shall live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But the midwives feared God [with profound reverence] and did not
        do as the king of Egypt commanded, but they let the boy babies live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the king of Egypt called for the midwives and said to them, \u201CWhy
        have you done this thing, and allowed the boy babies to live?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The midwives answered Pharaoh, \u201CBecause the Hebrew women are
        not like the Egyptian women; they are vigorous and give birth quickly and
        their babies are born before the midwife can get to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So God was good to the midwives, and the people [of Israel] multiplied
        and became very strong. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And because the midwives feared God [with profound reverence], He
        established families and households for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Pharaoh commanded all his people, saying, \u201CEvery son who
        is born [to the Hebrews] must be thrown into the Nile, but every daughter
        you shall keep alive.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Birth of Moses'
      title: The Birth of Moses
      number: 1
      content: '  Now a man of the house of Levi [the priestly tribe] went and took
        as his wife a daughter of Levi. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The woman conceived and gave birth to a son; and when she saw that
        he was [especially] beautiful and healthy, she hid him for three months [to
        protect him from the Egyptians]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When she could no longer hide him, she got him a basket (chest) made
        of papyrus reeds and covered it with tar and pitch [making it waterproof].
        Then she put the child in it and set it among the reeds by the bank of the
        Nile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And his sister [Miriam] stood some distance away to find out what
        would happen to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now the daughter of Pharaoh came down to bathe at the Nile, and [she,
        together with] her maidens walked along the river\u2019s bank; she saw the
        basket among the reeds and sent her maid [to get it], and she brought it
        to her.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When she opened it, she saw the child, and behold, the baby was crying.
        And she took pity on him and said, \u201CThis is one of the Hebrews\u2019
        children.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then his sister said to Pharaoh\u2019s daughter, \u201CShall I go
        and call a wet-nurse from the Hebrew women to nurse the child for you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Pharaoh\u2019s daughter said to her, \u201CGo ahead.\u201D So
        the girl went and called the child\u2019s mother. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Pharaoh\u2019s daughter said to her, \u201CTake this child away
        and nurse him for me, and I will give you your wages.\u201D So the woman
        took the child and nursed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the child grew, and she brought him to Pharaoh\u2019s daughter
        and he became her son. And she named him Moses, and said, \u201CBecause I
        drew him out of the water.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'One day, after Moses had grown [into adulthood], it happened that
        he went to his countrymen and looked [with compassion] at their hard labors;
        and he saw an Egyptian beating a Hebrew, one of his countrymen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He turned to look around, and seeing no one, he killed the Egyptian
        and hid him in the sand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He went out the next day and saw two Hebrew men fighting with each
        other; and he said to the aggressor, \u201CWhy are you striking your friend?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Moses Escapes to Midian'
      title: Moses Escapes to Midian
      number: 14
      content: "But the man said, \u201CWho made you a prince and a judge over us?
        Do you intend to kill me as you killed the Egyptian?\u201D Then Moses was
        afraid and said, \u201CCertainly this incident is known.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When Pharaoh heard about this matter, he tried to kill Moses. Then
        Moses fled from Pharaoh\u2019s presence and took refuge in the land of Midian,
        where he sat down by a well.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now the priest of Midian had seven daughters; and they came and drew
        water [from the well where Moses was resting] and filled the troughs to water
        their father\u2019s flock. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then shepherds came and drove them away, but Moses stood up and helped
        them and watered their flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When they came to Reuel (Jethro) their father, he said, \u201CHow
        is it that you have come back so soon today?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "They said, \u201CAn Egyptian saved us from the shepherds. He even
        drew water [from the well] for us and watered the flock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he said to his daughters, \u201CWhere is he? Why have you left
        the man behind? Invite him to have something to eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Moses was willing to remain with the man, and he gave Moses his daughter
        Zipporah [to be his wife]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "She gave birth to a son, and he named him Gershom (stranger); for
        he said, \u201CI have been a stranger in a foreign land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now it happened after a long time [about forty years] that the king
        of Egypt died. And the children of Israel (Jacob) groaned and sighed because
        of the bondage, and they cried out. And their cry for help because of their
        bondage ascended to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So God heard their groaning and God remembered His covenant with
        Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob (Israel). '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: God saw the sons of Israel, and God took notice [of them] and was
        concerned about them [knowing all, understanding all, remembering all].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Burning Bush'
      title: The Burning Bush
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Moses was keeping the flock of Jethro (Reuel) his father-in-law,
        the priest of Midian; and he led his flock to the west side of the wilderness
        and came to Horeb (Sinai), the mountain of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Angel of the Lord appeared to him in a blazing flame of fire
        from the midst of a bush; and he looked, and behold, the bush was on fire,
        yet it was not consumed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Moses said, \u201CI must turn away [from the flock] and see this
        great sight\u2014why the bush is not burned up.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "When the Lord saw that he turned away [from the flock] to look, God
        called to him from the midst of the bush and said, \u201CMoses, Moses!\u201D
        And he said, \u201CHere I am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then God said, \u201CDo not come near; take your sandals off your
        feet [out of respect], because the place on which you are standing is holy
        ground.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then He said, \u201CI am the God of your father, the God of Abraham,
        the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.\u201D Then Moses hid his face, because
        he was afraid to look at God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Lord said, \u201CI have in fact seen the affliction (suffering,
        desolation) of My people who are in Egypt, and have heard their cry because
        of their taskmasters (oppressors); for I know their pain and suffering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So I have come down to rescue them from the hand (power) of the Egyptians,
        and to bring them up from that land to a land [that is] good and spacious,
        to a land flowing with milk and honey [a land of plenty]\u2014to the place
        of the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Amorite, the Perizzite, the Hivite, and
        the Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Mission of Moses'
      title: The Mission of Moses
      number: 9
      content: 'Now, behold, the cry of the children of Israel has come to Me; and
        I have also seen how the Egyptians oppress them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore, come now, and I will send you to Pharaoh, and then bring
        My people, the children of Israel, out of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Moses said to God, \u201CWho am I, that I should go to Pharaoh,
        and that I should bring the children of Israel out of Egypt?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And God said, \u201CCertainly I will be with you, and this shall
        be the sign to you that it is I who have sent you: when you have brought
        the people out of Egypt, you shall serve and worship God at this mountain.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Moses said to God, \u201CBehold, when I come to the Israelites
        and say to them, \u2018The God of your fathers (ancestors) has sent me to
        you,\u2019 and they say to me, \u2018What is His name?\u2019 What shall I
        say to them?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "God said to Moses, \u201CI AM WHO I AM\u201D; and He said, \u201CYou
        shall say this to the Israelites, \u2018I AM has sent me to you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then God also said to Moses, \u201CThis is what you shall say to
        the Israelites, \u2018The Lord, the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham,
        the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob (Israel), has sent me to you.\u2019
        This is My Name forever, and this is My memorial [name] to all generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Go, gather the elders (tribal leaders) of Israel together, and say
        to them, \u2018The Lord, the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, of
        Isaac, and of Jacob, appeared to me, saying, \u201CI am indeed concerned
        about you and what has been done to you in Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So I said I will bring you up out of the suffering and oppression
        of Egypt to the land of the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Amorite, the Perizzite,
        the Hivite, and the Jebusite, to a land flowing with milk and honey.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The elders [of the tribes] will listen and pay attention to what
        you say; and you, with the elders of Israel, shall go to the king of Egypt
        and you shall say to him, \u2018The Lord, the God of the Hebrews, has met
        with us; so now, please, [we ask and plead with you,] let us go on a three
        days\u2019 journey into the wilderness, so that we may sacrifice to the Lord
        our God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But I know that the king of Egypt will not let you go unless [he
        is forced] by a strong hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So I will reach out My hand and strike Egypt with all My wonders
        which I shall do in the midst of it; and after that he will let you go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And I will grant this people favor and respect in the sight of the
        Egyptians; therefore, it shall be that when you go, you will not go empty-handed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But every woman shall [insistently] ask her neighbor and any woman
        who lives in her house, for articles of silver and articles of gold, and
        clothing; and you shall put them on your sons and daughters. In this way
        you are to plunder the Egyptians [leaving bondage with great possessions
        that are rightfully yours].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moses Given Powers'
      title: Moses Given Powers
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Moses answered [the Lord] and said, \u201CWhat if they will
        not believe me or take seriously what I say? For they may say, \u2018The
        Lord has not appeared to you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Lord said to him, \u201CWhat is that in your hand?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CA staff.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then He said, \u201CThrow it on the ground.\u201D So Moses threw
        it on the ground, and it became a [living] serpent [like the royal symbol
        on the crown of Pharaoh]; and Moses ran from it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the Lord said to Moses, \u201CReach out your hand and grasp it
        by the tail.\u201D So he reached out his hand and caught it, and it became
        a staff in his hand\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "[\u201CYou shall do this,\u201D said the Lord,] \u201Cso that the
        elders may believe that the Lord, the God of their fathers, the God of Abraham,
        the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has [most certainly] appeared to
        you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The Lord also said to him, \u201CPut your hand into your robe [where
        it covers your chest].\u201D So he put his hand into his robe, and when he
        took it out, his hand was leprous, as white as snow. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then God said, \u201CPut your hand into your robe again.\u201D So
        he put his hand back into his robe, and when he took it out, it was restored
        [and was] like the rest of his body. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CIf they will not believe you or pay attention to the evidence
        of the first sign, they may believe the evidence of the second sign. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But if they will not believe these two signs or pay attention to
        what you say, you are to take some water from the Nile and pour it on the
        dry ground; and the water which you take out of the river will turn into
        blood on the dry ground.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Moses said to the Lord, \u201CPlease, Lord, I am not a man of
        words (eloquent, fluent), neither before nor since You have spoken to Your
        servant; for I am slow of speech and tongue.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The Lord said to him, \u201CWho has made man\u2019s mouth? Or who
        makes the mute or the deaf, or the seeing or the blind? Is it not I, the
        Lord? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now then go, and I, even I, will be with your mouth, and will teach
        you what you shall say.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Aaron to Speak for Moses'
      title: Aaron to Speak for Moses
      number: 13
      content: "But he said, \u201CPlease my Lord, send the message [of rescue to
        Israel] by [someone else,] whomever else You will [choose].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the anger of the Lord was kindled and burned against Moses;
        He said, \u201CIs there not your brother, Aaron the Levite? I know that he
        speaks fluently. Also, he is coming out to meet you, and when he sees you,
        he will be overjoyed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You must speak to him and put the words in his mouth; I, even I,
        will be with your mouth and with his mouth, and I will teach you what you
        are to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover, he shall speak for you to the people; he will act as a
        mouthpiece for you, and you will be as God to him [telling him what I say
        to you]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "You shall take in your hand this staff, with which you shall perform
        the signs [the miracles which prove I sent you].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Moses went away and returned to Jethro his father-in-law, and
        said to him, \u201CPlease, let me go back so that I may return to my relatives
        in Egypt, and see if they are still alive.\u201D And Jethro said to Moses,
        \u201CGo in peace.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses in Midian, \u201CGo back to Egypt, for
        all the men who were seeking your life [for killing the Egyptian] are dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Moses took his wife [Zipporah] and his sons [Gershom and Eliezer]
        and seated them on donkeys, and returned to the land of Egypt. Moses also
        took the staff of God in his hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The Lord said to Moses, \u201CWhen you return to Egypt, see that
        you perform before Pharaoh all the wonders (miracles) which I have put in
        your hand, but I will harden his heart and make him stubborn so that he will
        not let the people go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then you shall say to Pharaoh, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CIsrael
        is My son, My firstborn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So I say to you, \u2018Let My son go so that he may serve Me\u2019;
        and if you refuse to let him go, behold, I will kill your son, your firstborn.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now it happened at the lodging place, that the Lord met Moses and
        sought to kill him [making him deathly ill because he had not circumcised
        one of his sons]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Zipporah took a flint knife and cut off the foreskin of her
        son and threw it at Moses\u2019 feet, and said, \u201CIndeed you are a husband
        of blood to me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So He let Moses alone [to recover]. At that time Zipporah said, \u201CYou
        are a husband of blood\u201D\u2014because of the circumcision.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The Lord said to Aaron, \u201CGo into the wilderness to meet Moses.\u201D
        So he went and met him at the mountain of God (Sinai) and kissed him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Moses told Aaron all the words of the Lord with which He had sent
        him, and all the signs that He had commanded him to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Moses and Aaron went [into Egypt] and assembled all the elders
        of the Israelites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'and Aaron said all the words which the Lord had spoken to Moses.
        Then Moses performed the signs [given to him by God] before the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: So the people believed; and when they heard that the Lord was concerned
        about the Israelites and that He had looked [with compassion] on their suffering,
        then they bowed their heads and worshiped [the Lord].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Labor Increased"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Labor Increased"
      number: 1
      content: "  Afterward Moses and Aaron came and said to Pharaoh, \u201CThus
        says the Lord, the God of Israel, \u2018Let My people go, so that they may
        celebrate a feast to Me in the wilderness.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But Pharaoh said, \u201CWho is the Lord that I should obey His voice
        to let Israel go? I do not know the Lord, nor will I let Israel go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then they said, \u201CThe God of the Hebrews has met with us. Please,
        let us go on a three days\u2019 journey into the wilderness and sacrifice
        to the Lord our God, so that He does not discipline us with pestilence or
        with the sword.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the king of Egypt said to Moses and Aaron, \u201CWhy do you take
        the people away from their work? Get back to your burdens!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Pharaoh said, \u201CLook, the people of the land are now many, and
        you would have them stop their work!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The very same day Pharaoh gave orders to the [Egyptian] taskmasters
        in charge of the people and their [Hebrew] foremen, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou will no longer give the people straw to make brick as before;
        let them go and gather straw for themselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But the number of bricks which they were making before, you shall
        [still] require of them; you are not to reduce it in the least. For they
        are idle and lazy; that is why they cry, \u2018Let us go and sacrifice to
        our God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Let labor be heavier on the men, and let them work [hard] at it so
        that they will pay no attention to [their God\u2019s] lying words.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the [Egyptian] taskmasters [in charge] of the people and their
        [Hebrew] foremen went out and said to the people, \u201CThus says Pharaoh,
        \u2018I will not give you any straw. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Go, get straw for yourselves wherever you can find it, but your work
        [quota] will not be reduced in the least.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the people were scattered throughout the land of Egypt to gather
        stubble to use for straw. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the taskmasters pressured them, saying, \u201CFinish your work,
        [fulfill] your daily quotas, just as when there was straw [given to you].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the Hebrew foremen, whom Pharaoh\u2019s taskmasters had set over
        them, were beaten and were asked, \u201CWhy have you not fulfilled your required
        quota of making bricks yesterday and today, as before?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the Hebrew foremen came to Pharaoh and cried, \u201CWhy do you
        deal like this with your servants? "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "No straw is given to your servants, yet they say to us, \u2018Make
        bricks!\u2019 And look, your servants are being beaten, but it is the fault
        of your own people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Pharaoh said, \u201CYou are lazy, very lazy and idle! That is
        why you say, \u2018Let us go and sacrifice to the Lord.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Get out now and get to work; for no straw will be given to you, yet
        you are to deliver the same quota of bricks.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The Hebrew foremen saw that they were in a bad situation because
        they were told, \u201CYou must not reduce [in the least] your daily quota
        of bricks.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "When they left Pharaoh\u2019s presence, the foremen met Moses and
        Aaron, who were waiting for them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the foremen said to them, \u201CMay the Lord look upon you and
        judge you, because you have made us odious (something hated) in the sight
        of Pharaoh and his servants, and you have put a sword in their hand to kill
        us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Moses turned again to the Lord and said, \u201CO Lord, why have
        You brought harm and oppression to this people? Why did You ever send me?
        [I cannot understand Your purpose!] "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Ever since I came to Pharaoh to speak in Your name, he has harmed
        and oppressed this people, and You have done nothing at all to rescue Your
        people.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Promises Action'
      title: God Promises Action
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CNow you shall see what I will
        do to Pharaoh; for under compulsion he will [not only] let them go, but under
        compulsion he will drive them out of his land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then God spoke further to Moses and said to him, \u201CI am the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I appeared to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob (Israel) as God Almighty
        [El Shaddai], but by My name, Lord, I did not make Myself known to them [in
        acts and great miracles]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I also established My covenant with them, to give them the land of
        Canaan, the land in which they lived as strangers (temporary residents, foreigners). '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I have also heard the groaning of the sons of Israel, whom the
        Egyptians have enslaved, and I have [faithfully] remembered My covenant [with
        Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore, say to the children of Israel, \u2018I am the Lord, and
        I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, and I will
        free you from their bondage. I will redeem and rescue you with an outstretched
        (vigorous, powerful) arm and with great acts of judgment [against Egypt]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then I will take you for My people, and I will be your God; and you
        shall know that I am the Lord your God, who redeemed you and brought you
        out from under the burdens of the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "I will bring you to the land which I swore to give to Abraham, Isaac,
        and Jacob (Israel); and I will give it to you as a possession. I am the Lord
        [you have the promise of My changeless omnipotence and faithfulness].\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Moses told this to the Israelites, but they did not listen to him
        because of their impatience and despondency, and because of their forced
        labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CGo, tell Pharaoh king of Egypt to let the children of Israel
        go out of his land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Moses said to the Lord, \u201CLook, [my own people] the Israelites
        have not listened to me; so how then will Pharaoh listen to me, for I am
        unskilled and inept in speech?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Heads of Israel'
      title: The Heads of Israel
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses and Aaron, and gave them a command concerning
        the Israelites and Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring the Israelites out of
        the land of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "These are the heads of their fathers\u2019 households. The sons of
        Reuben, Israel\u2019s (Jacob\u2019s) firstborn: Hanoch and Pallu, Hezron
        and Carmi; these are the families of Reuben. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The sons of Simeon: Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul
        the son of a Canaanite woman; these are the families of Simeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These are the names of the sons of Levi according to their births:
        Gershon, Kohath, and Merari; and Levi lived a hundred and thirty-seven years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sons of Gershon: Libni and Shimei, by their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The sons of Kohath: Amram (Moses\u2019 father), Izhar, Hebron, and
        Uzziel; and Kohath lived a hundred and thirty-three years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of Levi
        according to their generations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Amram married his father\u2019s sister Jochebed, and she gave birth
        to Aaron and Moses; and Amram lived a hundred and thirty-seven years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The sons of Izhar: Korah, Nepheg, and Zichri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Uzziel: Mishael, Elzaphan, and Sithri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Aaron married Elisheba, the daughter of Amminadab and the sister
        of Nahshon, and she gave birth to Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sons of Korah: Assir, Elkanah, and Abiasaph. These are the [extended]
        families of the Korahites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Eleazar, Aaron\u2019s son, married one of the daughters of Putiel,
        and she gave birth to Phinehas. These are the heads of the fathers\u2019
        households of the Levites by their families. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "These are [the same] Aaron and Moses to whom the Lord said, \u201CBring
        the children of Israel out of the land of Egypt by their armies.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'They were the ones who spoke to Pharaoh king of Egypt about bringing
        the Israelites out of Egypt; these are [the same] Moses and Aaron.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Now it happened on the day when the Lord spoke to Moses in the land
        of Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that He said, \u201CI am the Lord; tell Pharaoh king of Egypt everything
        that I say to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "But Moses said before the Lord, \u201CLook, I am unskilled and inept
        in speech; how then will Pharaoh listen to me and pay attention to what I
        say?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: \u201CI Will Stretch Out My Hand\u201D"
      title: "\u201CI Will Stretch Out My Hand\u201D"
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CNow hear this: I make you as
        God to Pharaoh [to declare My will and purpose to him]; and your brother
        Aaron shall be your prophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall speak all that I command you, and your brother Aaron shall
        tell Pharaoh to let the children of Israel go out of his land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I will make Pharaoh\u2019s heart hard, and multiply My signs
        and My wonders (miracles) in the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Pharaoh will not listen to you, and I shall lay My hand on Egypt
        and bring out My hosts [like a defensive army, tribe by tribe], My people
        the children of Israel, out of the land of Egypt by great acts of judgment
        (the plagues). '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The Egyptians shall know that I am the Lord, when I stretch out My
        hand on Egypt and bring out the children of Israel from among them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Moses and Aaron did so; just as the Lord commanded them, so they
        did. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Aaron\u2019s Rod Becomes a Serpent"
      title: "Aaron\u2019s Rod Becomes a Serpent"
      number: 7
      content: 'Now Moses was eighty years old and Aaron eighty-three years old when
        they spoke to Pharaoh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now the Lord said to Moses and Aaron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWhen Pharaoh says to you, \u2018Work a miracle [to prove your
        authority],\u2019 then you say to Aaron, \u2018Take your staff and throw
        it down before Pharaoh, so that it may become a serpent.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Moses and Aaron came to Pharaoh, and did just as the Lord had
        commanded; Aaron threw down his staff before Pharaoh and his servants, and
        it became a serpent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Pharaoh called for the wise men [skilled in magic and omens]
        and the sorcerers [skilled in witchcraft], and they also, these magicians
        (soothsayer-priests) of Egypt, did the same with their secret arts and enchantments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For every man threw down his staff and they turned into serpents;
        but Aaron\u2019s staff swallowed up their staffs. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Water Is Turned to Blood'
      title: Water Is Turned to Blood
      number: 13
      content: "Yet Pharaoh\u2019s heart was hardened and he would not listen to
        them, just as the Lord had said.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CPharaoh\u2019s heart is hard;
        he refuses to let the people go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Go to Pharaoh in the morning as he is going out to the water, and
        wait for him on the bank of the Nile; and you shall take in your hand the
        staff that was turned into a serpent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "You shall say to him, \u2018The Lord, the God of the Hebrews, has
        sent me to you, saying, \u201CLet My people go, so that they may serve Me
        in the wilderness. But behold, you have not listened until now.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Thus says the Lord, \u201CBy this you shall know and recognize and
        acknowledge that I am the Lord: look, with the staff in my hand I will strike
        the water in the Nile, and it shall be turned to blood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The fish in the Nile will die, and the Nile will become foul, and
        the Egyptians will not be able to drink water from the Nile.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CSay to Aaron, \u2018Take your
        staff and stretch out your hand over the waters of Egypt, over their rivers,
        over their streams, over their pools, and over all their reservoirs of water,
        so that they may become blood; and there shall be blood throughout all the
        land of Egypt, in containers both of wood and of stone.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Moses and Aaron did as the Lord commanded; Aaron lifted up the
        staff and struck the waters in the Nile, in the sight of Pharaoh and in the
        sight of his servants, and all the water that was in the Nile was turned
        into blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The fish in the Nile died, and the river became foul smelling, and
        the Egyptians could not drink its water, and there was blood throughout all
        the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But the magicians of Egypt did the same by their secret arts and
        enchantments; so Pharaoh\u2019s heart was hardened, and he did not listen
        to Moses and Aaron, just as the Lord had said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then Pharaoh turned and went into his house, and he did not take
        even this [divine sign] to heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So all the Egyptians dug near the river for water to drink, because
        they could not drink the water of the Nile. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Seven days passed after the Lord had struck the Nile.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Frogs over the Land'
      title: Frogs over the Land
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo to Pharaoh and say to him,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CLet My people go, so that they may serve
        Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'However, if you refuse to let them go, hear this: I am going to strike
        your entire land with frogs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Nile will swarm with frogs, which will come up and go into your
        home, into your bedroom and on to your bed, and into the houses of your servants
        and on your people, and into your ovens and your kneading bowls. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So the frogs will come up on you and on your people and all your
        servants.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CSay to Aaron, \u2018Stretch out
        your hand with your staff over the rivers, over the streams and canals, over
        the pools [among the reeds], and make frogs come up on the land of Egypt.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Aaron stretched out his hand [with his staff] over the waters
        of Egypt, and the frogs came up and covered the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But the magicians (soothsayer-priests) did the same thing with their
        secret arts and enchantments, and brought up [more] frogs on the land of
        Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron and said, \u201CPlead with
        the Lord that He may take away the frogs from me and my people; and I will
        let the people go, so that they may sacrifice to the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Moses said to Pharaoh, \u201CI am entirely at your service: when
        shall I plead [with the Lord] for you and your servants and your people,
        so that the frogs may leave you and your houses and remain only in the Nile?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then Pharaoh said, \u201CTomorrow.\u201D Moses replied, \u201CMay
        it be as you say, so that you may know [without any doubt] and acknowledge
        that there is no one like the Lord our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The frogs will leave you and your houses and leave your servants
        and your people; they will remain only in the Nile.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Moses and Aaron left Pharaoh, and Moses cried out to the Lord
        [as he had agreed to do] concerning the frogs which God had inflicted on
        Pharaoh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The Lord did as Moses asked, and the frogs died out of the houses,
        out of the courtyards and villages, and out of the fields. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So they piled them up in heaps, and the land was detestable and stank. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Plagues of Gnats and Insects'
      title: The Plagues of Gnats and Insects
      number: 15
      content: 'But when Pharaoh saw that there was [temporary] relief, he hardened
        his heart and would not listen or pay attention to them, just as the Lord
        had said.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CSay to Aaron, \u2018Stretch out
        your staff and strike the dust of the ground, and it will become [biting]
        gnats (lice) throughout the land of Egypt.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They did so; Aaron stretched out his hand with his staff and struck
        the dust of the earth, and there were [biting] gnats on man and animal. All
        the dust of the land became gnats through all the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The magicians (soothsayer-priests) tried by their secret arts and
        enchantments to create gnats, but they could not; and there were gnats on
        man and animal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then the magicians said to Pharaoh, \u201CThis is the [supernatural]
        finger of God.\u201D But Pharaoh\u2019s heart was hardened and he would not
        listen to them, just as the Lord had said.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Now the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGet up early in the morning and
        stand before Pharaoh as he is coming out to the water [of the Nile], and
        say to him, \u2018Thus says the Lord, \u201CLet My people go, so that they
        may serve Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For if you do not let My people go, hear this: I will send swarms
        of [bloodsucking] insects on you and on your servants and on your people
        and into your houses; and the houses of the Egyptians will be full of swarms
        of insects, as well as the ground on which they stand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But on that day I will separate and set apart the land of Goshen,
        where My people are living, so that no swarms of insects will be there, so
        that you may know [without any doubt] and acknowledge that I, the Lord, am
        in the midst of the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will put a division (distinction) between My people and your people.
        By tomorrow this sign shall be in evidence.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the Lord did so. And there came heavy and oppressive swarms
        of [bloodsucking] insects into the house of Pharaoh and his servants\u2019
        houses; in all the land of Egypt the land was corrupted and ruined because
        of the [great invasion of] insects.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Pharaoh called for Moses and Aaron and said, \u201CGo, sacrifice
        to your God [here] in the land [of Egypt].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But Moses said, \u201CIt is not right [or even possible] to do that,
        for we will sacrifice to the Lord our God what is repulsive and unacceptable
        to the Egyptians [that is, animals that the Egyptians consider sacred]. If
        we sacrifice what is repulsive and unacceptable to the Egyptians, will they
        not riot and stone us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "We must go a three days\u2019 journey into the wilderness and sacrifice
        to the Lord our God as He commands us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So Pharaoh said, \u201CI will let you go, so that you may sacrifice
        to the Lord your God in the wilderness; only you shall not go very far away.
        Plead [with your God] for me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Moses said, \u201CI am going to leave you, and I will urgently petition
        (pray, entreat) the Lord that the swarms of insects may leave Pharaoh, his
        servants, and his people tomorrow; only do not let Pharaoh act deceitfully
        again by not letting the people go to sacrifice to the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So Moses left Pharaoh and prayed to the Lord [on behalf of Pharaoh]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The Lord did as Moses asked, and removed the swarms of [bloodsucking]
        insects from Pharaoh, from his servants and from his people; not one remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: But Pharaoh hardened his heart this time also, and he did not let
        the people go.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Egyptian Livestock Die'
      title: Egyptian Livestock Die
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo to Pharaoh and tell him,
        \u2018Thus says the Lord, the God of the Hebrews: \u201CLet My people go,
        so that they may serve Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But if you refuse to let them go and continue to hold them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "now hear this: the hand of the Lord will fall on your livestock which
        are out in the field, on the horses, the donkeys, the camels, the herds,
        and the flocks\u2014a horrible plague shall come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the Lord will make a distinction between the livestock of Israel
        and the livestock of Egypt, so that nothing that belongs to the Israelites
        will die.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The Lord set a [definite] time, saying, \u201CTomorrow the Lord will
        do this thing in the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the Lord did this thing the next day, and all [kinds of] the
        livestock of Egypt died; but of the livestock of the Israelites, not one
        died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Plague of Boils'
      title: The Plague of Boils
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Pharaoh sent [men to investigate], and not even one of the livestock
        of the Israelites had died. But the heart of Pharaoh was hardened [and his
        mind was firmly set], and he did not let the people go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses and Aaron, \u201CTake handfuls of soot
        from the brick kiln, and let Moses throw it toward the sky in the sight of
        Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "It will become fine dust over the entire land of Egypt, and it will
        become boils breaking out in sores on man and animal in all the land [occupied
        by the Egyptians].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So they took soot from the kiln, and stood before Pharaoh; and Moses
        threw it toward the sky, and it became boils erupting in sores on man and
        animal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The magicians (soothsayer-priests) could not stand before Moses because
        of the boils, for the boils were on the magicians as well as on all the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the Lord hardened the heart of Pharaoh, and he did not listen
        or pay attention to them, just as the Lord had told Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGet up early in the morning and
        stand before Pharaoh and say to him, \u2018Thus says the Lord, the God of
        the Hebrews, \u201CLet My people go, so that they may serve Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For this time I will send all My plagues on you [in full force,]
        and on your servants and on your people, so that you may know [without any
        doubt] and acknowledge that there is no one like Me in all the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For by now I could have put out My hand and struck you and your people
        with a pestilence, and you would then have been cut off (obliterated) from
        the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Plague of Hail'
      title: The Plague of Hail
      number: 16
      content: 'But indeed for this very reason I have allowed you to live, in order
        to show you My power and in order that My name may be proclaimed throughout
        all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Since you are still [arrogantly] exalting yourself [in defiance]
        against My people by not letting them go, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'hear this: tomorrow about this time I will send a very heavy and
        dreadful hail, such as has not been seen in Egypt from the day it was founded
        until now. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now therefore send [a message], bring your livestock and whatever
        you have in the field to safety. Every man and animal that is in the field
        and is not brought home shall be struck by the hail and shall die.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then everyone among the servants of Pharaoh who feared the word of
        the Lord made his servants and his livestock flee into the houses and shelters; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'but everyone who ignored and did not take seriously the word of the
        Lord left his servants and his livestock in the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now the Lord said to Moses, \u201CStretch out your hand [with your
        staff] toward the sky, so that there may be hail in all the land of Egypt,
        on man and on animal and on all the vegetation of the field, throughout the
        land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Moses stretched out his staff toward the sky, and the Lord sent thunder
        and hail, and lightning (fireballs) ran down to the earth and along the ground.
        And the Lord rained hail on the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So there was hail, and lightning (fireballs) flashing intermittently
        in the midst of the extremely heavy hail, such as had not been in all the
        land of Egypt since it became a nation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The hail struck down everything that was in the field throughout
        all the land of Egypt, both man and animal; the hail struck and beat down
        all the plants in the field and shattered every tree in the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Only in the land of Goshen, where the children of Israel lived, was
        there no hail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then Pharaoh sent for Moses and Aaron, and said to them, \u201CI
        have sinned this time; the Lord is righteous, and I and my people are wicked. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Pray and entreat the Lord, for there has been enough of God\u2019s
        thunder and hail; I will let you go, and you shall stay here no longer.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Moses said to him, \u201CAs soon as I leave the city, I will stretch
        out my hands to the Lord; the thunder will cease and there will be no more
        hail, so that you may know [without any doubt] and acknowledge that the earth
        is the Lord\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "But as for you and your servants, I know that you do not yet fear
        the Lord God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '(Now the flax and the barley were battered and ruined [by the hail],
        because the barley was in the ear (ripe, but soft) and the flax was in bud, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'but the wheat and spelt (coarse wheat) were not battered and ruined,
        because they ripen late in the season.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So Moses left the city and Pharaoh, and stretched out his hands to
        the Lord; then the thunder and hail ceased, and rain no longer poured on
        the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But when Pharaoh saw that the rain and the hail and the thunder had
        ceased, he sinned again and hardened his heart, both he and his servants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Pharaoh\u2019s heart was hardened, and he did not let the Israelites
        go, just as the Lord had said through Moses."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Plague of Locusts'
      title: The Plague of Locusts
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo to Pharaoh, for I have hardened
        his heart and the heart of his servants [making them determined and unresponsive],
        so that I may exhibit My signs [of divine power] among them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and that you may recount and explain in the hearing of your son,
        and your grandson, what I have done [repeatedly] to make a mockery of the
        Egyptians\u2014My signs [of divine power] which I have done among them\u2014so
        that you may know [without any doubt] and recognize [clearly] that I am the
        Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Moses and Aaron went to Pharaoh and said to him, \u201CThus says
        the Lord, the God of the Hebrews: \u2018How long will you refuse to humble
        yourself before Me? Let My people go, so that they may serve Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For if you refuse to let My people go, then hear this: tomorrow I
        will bring [migratory] locusts into your country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They shall cover the [visible] surface of the land, so that no one
        will be able to see the ground, and they will eat the rest of what has remained\u2014that
        is, the vegetation left after the hail\u2014and they will eat every one of
        your trees that grows in the field; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "your houses and those of all your servants and of all the Egyptians
        shall be filled with locusts, as neither your fathers nor your grandfathers
        have seen, from their birth until this day.\u2019\u2009\u201D Then Moses
        turned and left Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Pharaoh\u2019s servants said to him, \u201CHow long shall this man
        be a trap to us? Let the men go, so that they may serve the Lord their God.
        Do you not realize that Egypt is destroyed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Moses and Aaron were brought back to Pharaoh, and he said to them,
        \u201CGo, serve the Lord your God! Who specifically are the ones that are
        going?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Moses said, \u201CWe will go with our young and our old, with our
        sons and our daughters, with our flocks and our herds [all of us and all
        that we have], for we must hold a feast to the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Pharaoh said to them, \u201CThe Lord be with you [to help you], if
        I ever let you go with your children [because you will never return]! Look
        [be forewarned], you have an evil plan in mind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "No! Go now, you who are men, [without your families] and serve the
        Lord, if that is what you want.\u201D So Moses and Aaron were driven from
        Pharaoh\u2019s presence.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CStretch out your hand over the
        land of Egypt for the locusts, so that they may come up on the land of Egypt
        and eat all the plants of the land, all that the hail has left.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Moses stretched out his staff over the land of Egypt, and the
        Lord brought an east wind on the land all that day and all that night; when
        it was morning, the east wind had brought the [swarms of] locusts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The locusts came up over all the land of Egypt and settled down in
        the whole territory, a very dreadful mass of them; never before were there
        such locusts as these, nor will there ever be again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For they covered the [visible] surface of the land, so that the ground
        was darkened; and they ate every plant of the land and all the fruit of the
        trees which the hail had left. There remained not a green thing on the trees
        or the plants of the field throughout all the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Pharaoh hurried to call for Moses and Aaron, and he said, \u201CI
        have sinned against the Lord your God and against you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now therefore, please forgive my sin only this once [more], and pray
        and entreat the Lord your God, so that He will remove this [plague of] death
        from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Moses left Pharaoh and entreated the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So the Lord shifted the wind to a violent west wind which lifted
        up the locusts and drove them into the Red Sea; not one locust remained within
        the border of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Darkness over the Land'
      title: Darkness over the Land
      number: 20
      content: "But the Lord hardened Pharaoh\u2019s heart [so that it was even more
        resolved and obstinate], and he did not let the Israelites go.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CStretch out your hand toward the
        sky, so that darkness may come over the land of Egypt, a darkness which [is
        so awful that it] may be felt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Moses stretched out his hand toward the sky, and for three days
        a thick darkness was all over the land of Egypt [no sun, no moon, no stars]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The Egyptians could not see one another, nor did anyone leave his
        place for three days, but all the Israelites had [supernatural] light in
        their dwellings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Pharaoh called to Moses, and said, \u201CGo, serve the Lord;
        only your flocks and your herds must be left behind. Even your children may
        go with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But Moses said, \u201CYou must also let us have sacrifices and burnt
        offerings, so that we may sacrifice them to the Lord our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore, our livestock must also go with us; not one hoof shall
        be left behind, for we must take some of them to serve the Lord our God.
        Even we do not know with what we will serve the Lord until we arrive there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "But the Lord hardened Pharaoh\u2019s heart, and he was not willing
        to let them go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Pharaoh said to Moses, \u201CGet away from me! See that you
        never enter my presence again, for on the day that you see my face again
        you will die!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CYou are correct; I will never see your face
        again!\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Last Plague'
      title: The Last Plague
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CI will bring yet one more plague
        on Pharaoh and on Egypt; after that he will let you go. When he lets you
        go, he will most certainly drive you out of here completely. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Speak so that all of the people [of Israel] may hear, and tell every
        man to ask from his neighbor, and every woman to ask from her neighbor, articles
        of silver, and articles of gold.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The Lord gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians. Moreover,
        the man Moses was greatly esteemed in the land of Egypt, [both] in the sight
        of Pharaoh\u2019s servants and in the sight of the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018At midnight I am
        going out into the midst of Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and all the firstborn in the land [the pride, hope, and joy] of Egypt
        shall die, from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sits on his throne, to the firstborn
        of the slave girl who is behind the hand-mill, and all the firstborn of cattle
        as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'There shall be a great cry [of heartache and sorrow] throughout the
        land of Egypt, such as has never been before and such as shall never be again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But not even a dog will threaten any of the Israelites, whether man
        or animal, so that you may know [without any doubt] and acknowledge how the
        Lord makes a distinction between Egypt and Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All these servants of yours will come down to me and bow down before
        me, saying, \u2018Get out, you and all the people who follow you.\u2019 After
        that I will leave.\u201D And he left Pharaoh in the heat of anger.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CPharaoh will not listen to you,
        so that My wonders (miracles) may be multiplied in the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Moses and Aaron did all these wonders (miracles) before Pharaoh;
        yet the Lord hardened Pharaoh\u2019s heart, and he did not let the Israelites
        go out of his land."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Passover Lamb'
      title: The Passover Lamb
      number: 1
      content: '  The Lord said to Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CThis month shall be the beginning of months to you; it is to
        be the first month of the year to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Tell all the congregation of Israel, \u2018On the tenth [day] of
        this month they are to take a lamb or young goat for themselves, according
        to [the size of] the household of which he is the father, a lamb or young
        goat for each household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now if the household is too small for a lamb [to be consumed], let
        him and his next door neighbor take one according to the number of people
        [in the households]; according to what each man can eat, you are to divide
        the lamb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Your lamb or young goat shall be [perfect] without blemish or bodily
        defect, a male a year old; you may take it from the sheep or from the goats. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall keep it until the fourteenth day of the same month, then
        the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel is to slaughter it at twilight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Moreover, they shall take some of the blood and put it on the two
        doorposts and on the lintel [above the door] of the houses in which they
        eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They shall eat the meat that same night, roasted in fire, and they
        shall eat it with unleavened bread and bitter herbs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Do not eat any of it raw or boiled in water, but roasted in fire\u2014both
        its head and its legs, along with its inner parts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall let none of the meat remain until the morning, and anything
        that remains left over until morning, you shall burn completely in the fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now you are to eat it in this manner: [be prepared for a journey]
        with your loins girded [that is, with the outer garment tucked into the band],
        your sandals on your feet, and your staff in your hand; you shall eat it
        quickly\u2014it is the Lord\u2019s Passover. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For I [the Lord] will pass through the land of Egypt on this night,
        and will strike down all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both man and
        animal; against all the gods of Egypt I will execute judgments [exhibiting
        their worthlessness]. I am the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Feast of Unleavened Bread'
      title: Feast of Unleavened Bread
      number: 13
      content: 'The blood shall be a sign for you on [the doorposts of] the houses
        where you live; when I see the blood I shall pass over you, and no affliction
        shall happen to you to destroy you when I strike the land of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2018Now this day will be a memorial to you, and you shall keep
        it as a feast to the Lord; throughout your generations you are to celebrate
        it as an ordinance forever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '[In the celebration of the Passover in future years,] seven days
        you shall eat unleavened bread, but on the first day you shall remove the
        leaven from your houses [because it represents the spread of sin]; for whoever
        eats leavened bread on the first day through the seventh day, that person
        shall be cut off and excluded from [the atonement made for] Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "On the first day [of the feast] you shall have a holy and solemn
        assembly, and on the seventh day there shall be another holy and solemn assembly;
        no work of any kind shall be done on those days, except for the preparation
        of food which every person must eat\u2014only that may be done by you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You shall also observe the Feast of Unleavened Bread, because on
        this very day I brought your hosts [grouped according to tribal armies] out
        of the land of Egypt; therefore you shall observe this day throughout your
        generations as an ordinance forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month at evening,
        you shall eat unleavened bread, [and continue] until the twenty-first day
        of the month at evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Seven days no leaven shall be found in your houses; whoever eats
        what is leavened shall be cut off and excluded from [the atonement made for]
        the congregation of Israel, whether a stranger or native-born. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "You shall eat nothing leavened; in all your dwellings you shall eat
        unleavened bread.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Moses called for all the elders of Israel and said to them,
        \u201CGo and take a lamb for yourselves according to [the size of] your families
        and slaughter the Passover lamb. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: A Memorial of Redemption'
      title: A Memorial of Redemption
      number: 22
      content: 'You shall take a bunch of hyssop, dip it in the blood which is in
        the basin, and touch some of the blood to the lintel [above the doorway]
        and to the two doorposts; and none of you shall go outside the door of his
        house until morning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the Lord will pass through to strike the Egyptians; and when
        He sees the blood on the lintel [above the entry way] and on the two doorposts,
        the Lord will pass over the door and will not allow the destroyer to come
        into your houses to slay you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall observe this event [concerning Passover] as an ordinance
        for you and for your children forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When you enter the land which the Lord will give you, as He has promised,
        you shall keep and observe this service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "When your children say to you, \u2018What does this service mean
        to you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "you shall say, \u2018It is the sacrifice of the Lord\u2019s Passover,
        for He passed over the houses of the Israelites in Egypt when He struck the
        Egyptians, but spared our houses.\u2019\u2009\u201D And the people bowed
        [their heads] low and worshiped [God].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then the Israelites went and did [as they had been told]: just as
        the Lord had commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now it happened at midnight that the Lord struck every firstborn
        in the land of Egypt, from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sat on his throne
        to the firstborn of the prisoner who was in the dungeon, and all the firstborn
        of the cattle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Pharaoh got up in the night, he and all his servants and all the
        Egyptians, and there was a great cry [of heartache and sorrow] in Egypt,
        for there was no house where there was not someone dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then he called for Moses and Aaron at night and said, \u201CGet up,
        get out from among my people, both you and the Israelites; and go, serve
        the Lord, as you said. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Exodus of Israel'
      title: Exodus of Israel
      number: 32
      content: "Take both your flocks and your herds, as you have said, and go, and
        [ask your God to] bless me also.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The Egyptians [anxiously] urged the people [to leave], to send them
        out of the land quickly, for they said, \u201CWe will all be dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'So the people took their dough before it was leavened, their kneading
        bowls being bound up in their clothes on their shoulders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Now the Israelites had acted in accordance with the word of Moses;
        and they had asked the Egyptians for articles of silver and articles of gold,
        and clothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The Lord gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians, so
        that they gave them what they asked. And so they plundered the Egyptians
        [of those things].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Now the Israelites journeyed from Rameses to Succoth, about six hundred
        thousand men on foot, besides [the women and] the children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'A mixed multitude [of non-Israelites from foreign nations] also went
        with them, along with both flocks and herds, a very large number of livestock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And they baked unleavened cakes of the dough which they brought from
        Egypt; it was not leavened, since they were driven [quickly] from Egypt and
        could not delay, nor had they prepared any food for themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Now the period of time the children of Israel lived in Egypt was
        four hundred and thirty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: Ordinance of the Passover'
      title: Ordinance of the Passover
      number: 41
      content: 'At the end of the four hundred and thirty years, to that very day,
        all the hosts of the Lord [gathered into tribal armies] left the land of
        Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'It is a night of watching to be observed for the Lord for having
        brought them out of the land of Egypt; this [same] night is for the Lord,
        to be observed and celebrated by all the Israelites throughout their generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "The Lord said to Moses and Aaron, \u201CThis is the ordinance of
        the Passover: no foreigner is to eat it; "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "but every man\u2019s slave who is bought with money, after you have
        circumcised him, then he may eat it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'No stranger (temporary resident, foreigner) or hired servant shall
        eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'It is to be eaten inside one house; you shall not take any of the
        meat outside the house, nor shall you break any of its bones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The entire congregation of Israel shall keep and celebrate it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'If a stranger living temporarily among you wishes to celebrate the
        Passover to the Lord, all his males must be circumcised, and then he may
        participate and celebrate it like one that is born in the land. But no uncircumcised
        person may eat it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "The same law shall apply to the native-born and to the stranger who
        lives temporarily among you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Then all the Israelites did so; they did just as the Lord had commanded
        Moses and Aaron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: And on that very same day the Lord brought the Israelites out of the
        land of Egypt by their hosts (tribal armies).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Consecration of the Firstborn'
      title: Consecration of the Firstborn
      number: 1
      content: '  The Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSanctify to Me [that is, set apart for My purpose] every firstborn,
        the first offspring of every womb among the children of Israel, both of man
        and of animal; it is Mine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Moses said to the people, \u201CRemember [solemnly observe and commemorate]
        this day on which you came out of Egypt, out of the house of bondage and
        slavery; for by a strong and powerful hand the Lord brought you out of this
        place. And nothing leavened shall be eaten. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On this day in the month Abib, you are about to go onward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And it shall be when the Lord brings you into the land of the Canaanite,
        the Hittite, the Amorite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite, which He swore to
        your fathers to give you, a land [of abundance] flowing with milk and honey,
        that you shall keep and observe this rite (service) in this month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh
        day there shall be a feast to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Unleavened bread shall be eaten throughout the seven days; no leavened
        bread shall be seen with you, nor shall there be leaven within the borders
        of your territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You shall explain this to your son on that day, saying, \u2018It
        is because of what the Lord did for me when I came out of Egypt.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It shall serve as a sign to you on your hand (arm), and as a reminder
        on your forehead, so that the instruction (law) of the Lord may be in your
        mouth; for with a strong and powerful hand the Lord brought you out of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Therefore, you shall keep this ordinance at this time from year to
        year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CNow it shall be when the Lord brings you into the land of the
        Canaanite, as He swore to you and your fathers, and gives it to you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "you shall set apart and dedicate to the Lord all that first opens
        the womb. All the firstborn males of your livestock shall be the Lord\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Every firstborn of a donkey you shall redeem by [substituting] a
        lamb [as a sacrifice for it], but if you do not [wish to] redeem it, then
        you shall break its neck; and every firstborn among your sons you shall redeem
        [that is, \u2018buy back\u2019 from God with a suitable sacrifice]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And it shall be when your son asks you in time to come, saying, \u2018What
        does this mean?\u2019 you shall say to him, \u2018With a strong and powerful
        hand the Lord brought us out of Egypt, from the house of bondage and slavery. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For it happened, when Pharaoh stubbornly refused to let us go, that
        the Lord struck every firstborn in the land of Egypt, both the firstborn
        of man and the firstborn of animal. Therefore, I sacrifice to the Lord all
        the males, the first [to be born] of every womb, but every firstborn of my
        sons I redeem.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: God Leads the People'
      title: God Leads the People
      number: 16
      content: "So it shall serve as a sign and a reminder on your [left] hand (arm)
        and as frontlets between your eyes, for by a strong and powerful hand the
        Lord brought us out of Egypt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So it happened, when Pharaoh let the people go, God did not lead
        them by way of the land of the Philistines, even though it was nearer; for
        God said, \u201CThe people might change their minds when they see war [that
        is, that there will be war], and return to Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But God led the people around by the way of the wilderness toward
        the Red Sea; the sons of Israel went up in battle array (orderly ranks, marching
        formation) out of the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Moses took the bones of Joseph with him, for Joseph had solemnly
        ordered (placed under an oath) the Israelites, saying, \u201CGod will assuredly
        take care of you, and you must carry my bones away from here with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They journeyed from Succoth [in Goshen] and camped at Etham on the
        edge of the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The [presence of the] Lord was going before them by day in a pillar
        (column) of cloud to lead them along the way, and in a pillar of fire by
        night to give them light, so that they could travel by day and by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He did not withdraw the pillar of cloud by day, nor the pillar of
        fire by night, from going before the people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Pharaoh in Pursuit'
      title: Pharaoh in Pursuit
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTell the sons of Israel to turn back and camp in front of Pi-hahiroth,
        between Migdol and the sea. You shall camp in front of Baal-zephon, opposite
        it, by the sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For Pharaoh will say of the Israelites, \u2018They are wandering
        aimlessly in the land; the wilderness has shut them in.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "I will harden (make stubborn, defiant) Pharaoh\u2019s heart, so that
        he will pursue them; and I will be glorified and honored through Pharaoh
        and all his army, and the Egyptians shall know [without any doubt] and acknowledge
        that I am the Lord.\u201D And they did so.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When the king of Egypt was told that the people had fled, Pharaoh
        and his servants had a change of heart toward the people, and they said,
        \u201CWhat is this that we have done? We have let Israel go from serving
        us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Pharaoh harnessed horses to his war-chariots [for battle] and
        took his army with him; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and he took six hundred chosen war-chariots, and all the other war-chariots
        of Egypt with fighting charioteers over all of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord hardened the heart of Pharaoh, king of Egypt, and he pursued
        the Israelites, as they were leaving confidently and defiantly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Egyptians chased them with all the horses and war-chariots of
        Pharaoh, his horsemen and his army, and they overtook them as they camped
        by the sea, beside Pi-hahiroth, in front of Baal-zephon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As Pharaoh approached, the Israelites looked up and saw the Egyptians
        marching after them, and they were very frightened; so the Israelites cried
        out to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then they said to Moses, \u201CIs it because there are no graves
        in Egypt that you have taken us away to die in the wilderness? What is this
        that you have done to us by bringing us out of Egypt? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Sea Is Divided'
      title: The Sea Is Divided
      number: 12
      content: "Did we not say to you in Egypt, \u2018Leave us alone; let us serve
        the Egyptians?\u2019 For it would have been better for us to serve the Egyptians
        [as slaves] than to die in the wilderness.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Moses said to the people, \u201CDo not be afraid! Take your
        stand [be firm and confident and undismayed] and see the salvation of the
        Lord which He will accomplish for you today; for those Egyptians whom you
        have seen today, you will never see again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord will fight for you while you [only need to] keep silent
        and remain calm.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The Lord said to Moses, \u201CWhy do you cry to Me? Tell the sons
        of Israel to move forward [toward the sea]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'As for you, lift up your staff and stretch out your hand over the
        sea and divide it, so that the sons of Israel may go through the middle of
        the sea on dry land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As for Me, hear this: I will harden the hearts of the Egyptians,
        and they will go in [the sea] after them; and I will be glorified and honored
        through Pharaoh and all his army, and his war-chariots and his horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the Egyptians shall know [without any doubt] and acknowledge
        that I am the Lord, when I am glorified and honored through Pharaoh, through
        his war-chariots and his charioteers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The angel of God, who had been going in front of the camp of Israel,
        moved and went behind them. The pillar of the cloud moved from in front and
        stood behind them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So it came between the camp of Egypt and the camp of Israel. It was
        a cloud along with darkness [even by day to the Egyptians], but it gave light
        by night [to the Israelites]; so one [army] did not come near the other all
        night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Moses stretched out his hand over the sea; and the Lord swept
        the sea back by a strong east wind all that night and turned the seabed into
        dry land, and the waters were divided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Israelites went into the middle of the sea on dry land, and the
        waters formed a wall to them on their right hand and on their left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the Egyptians pursued them into the middle of the sea, even
        all Pharaoh\u2019s horses, his war-chariots and his charioteers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So it happened at the early morning watch [before dawn], that the
        Lord looked down on the army of the Egyptians through the pillar of fire
        and cloud and put them in a state of confusion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He made their chariot wheels hard to turn, and the chariots difficult
        to drive; so the Egyptians said, \u201CLet us flee from Israel, for the Lord
        is fighting for them against the Egyptians.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CStretch out your hand over the
        sea so that the waters may come back over the Egyptians, on their war-chariots
        and their charioteers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Moses stretched out his hand over the sea, and the sea returned
        to its normal flow at sunrise; and the Egyptians retreated right into it
        [being met by the returning water]; so the Lord overthrew the Egyptians and
        tossed them into the midst of the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The waters returned and covered the chariots and the charioteers,
        and all the army of Pharaoh that had gone into the sea after them; not even
        one of them survived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But the Israelites walked on dry land in the middle of the sea, and
        the waters formed a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The Lord saved Israel that day from the hand of the Egyptians, and
        Israel saw the Egyptians [lying] dead on the seashore. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: When Israel saw the great power which the Lord had used against the
        Egyptians, they feared the Lord [with reverence and awe-filled respect],
        and they believed in the Lord, and in His servant Moses.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Song of Moses and Israel'
      title: The Song of Moses and Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  Then Moses and the children of Israel sang this song to the Lord,
        singing,\u201CI will sing to the Lord, for He has triumphed gloriously;The
        horse and its rider He has thrown into the sea.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord is my strength and my song,And He has become my salvation;This
        is my God, and I will praise Him;My father\u2019s God, and I will exalt Him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Lord is a warrior;The Lord is His name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Pharaoh\u2019s chariots and his army He has thrown into the sea;His
        chosen captains are drowned in the Red Sea.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The deep [water] covers them;[Clad in armor] they sank into the depths
        like a stone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Your right hand, O Lord, is glorious in power;Your right hand, O
        Lord, shatters the enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the greatness of Your majesty You overthrow and annihilate those
        [adversaries] who rise [in rebellion] against You;You send out Your fury,
        and it consumes them like chaff.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'With the blast of Your nostrils the waters piled up,The flowing waters
        stood up like a mound;The deeps were congealed in the heart of the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The enemy said, \u2018I will pursue, I will overtake, I will divide
        the spoil;My desire shall be satisfied against them;I will draw my sword,
        my hand shall dispossess them and drive them out.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You blew with Your wind, the sea covered them;[Clad in armor] they
        sank like lead in the mighty waters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Who is like You among the gods, O Lord?Who is like You, majestic
        in holiness,Awesome in splendor, working wonders?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You stretched out Your right hand,The sea swallowed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You in Your lovingkindness and goodness have led the people whom
        You have redeemed;In Your strength You have guided them with care to Your
        holy habitation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The peoples have heard [about You], they tremble;Anguish and fear
        has gripped the inhabitants of Philistia.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the [tribal] chiefs of Edom were dismayed and horrified;The
        [mighty] leaders of Moab, trembling grips them;All the inhabitants of Canaan
        have melted away [in despair]\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Terror and dread fall on them;Because of the greatness of Your arm
        they are as still as a stone;Until Your people pass by and [into Canaan],
        O Lord,Until the people pass by whom You have purchased.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You will bring them [into the land of promise] and plant them on
        the mountain (Mt. Moriah in Jerusalem) of Your inheritance,The place, O Lord,
        You have made for Your dwelling [among them],The sanctuary, O Lord, which
        Your hands have established.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The Lord shall reign to eternity and beyond.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the horses of Pharaoh went with his war-chariots and his charioteers
        into the sea, and the Lord brought back the waters of the sea on them, but
        the sons of Israel walked on dry land in the middle of the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Miriam the prophetess, the sister of Aaron [and Moses], took
        a timbrel in her hand, and all the women followed her with timbrels and dancing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Lord Provides Water'
      title: The Lord Provides Water
      number: 21
      content: "Miriam answered them,\u201CSing to the Lord, for He has triumphed
        gloriously and is highly exalted;The horse and its rider He has hurled into
        the sea.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Moses led Israel from the Red Sea, and they went into the Wilderness
        of Shur; they went [a distance of] three days (about thirty-three miles)
        in the wilderness and found no water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then they came to Marah, but they could not drink its waters because
        they were bitter; therefore it was named Marah (bitter). '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The people [grew discontented and] grumbled at Moses, saying, \u201CWhat
        are we going to drink?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then he cried to the Lord [for help], and the Lord showed him a tree,
        [a branch of] which he threw into the waters, and the waters became sweet. 
        There the Lord made a statute and an ordinance for them, and there He tested
        them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "saying, \u201CIf you will diligently listen and pay attention to
        the voice of the Lord your God, and do what is right in His sight, and listen
        to His commandments, and keep [foremost in your thoughts and actively obey]
        all His precepts and statutes, then I will not put on you any of the diseases
        which I have put on the Egyptians; for I am the Lord who heals you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then the children of Israel came to Elim where there were twelve springs
        of water and seventy date palms, and they camped there beside the waters.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Lord Provides Manna'
      title: The Lord Provides Manna
      number: 1
      content: '  They set out from Elim, and all the congregation of Israel came
        to the Wilderness of Sin, which is between Elim and Sinai, on the fifteenth
        day of the second month after they left the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The whole congregation of the Israelites [grew discontented and]
        murmured and rebelled against Moses and Aaron in the wilderness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and the Israelites said to them, \u201CWould that we had died by
        the hand of the Lord in the land of Egypt, when we sat by the pots of meat
        and ate bread until we were full; for you have brought us out into this wilderness
        to kill this entire assembly with hunger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CBehold, I will cause bread to
        rain from heaven for you; the people shall go out and gather a day\u2019s
        portion every day, so that I may test them [to determine] whether or not
        they will walk [obediently] in My instruction (law). "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And it shall be that on the sixth day, they shall prepare to bring
        in twice as much as they gather daily [so that they will not need to gather
        on the seventh day].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Moses and Aaron said to all Israel, \u201CAt evening you shall
        know that the Lord has brought you out of the land of Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Lord Provides Meat'
      title: The Lord Provides Meat
      number: 7
      content: "and in the morning you will see the glory of the Lord, for He hears
        your murmurings against the Lord. What are we, that you murmur and rebel
        against us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Moses said, \u201CThis will happen when the Lord gives you meat to
        eat in the evening, and in the morning [enough] bread to be fully satisfied,
        because the Lord has heard your murmurings against Him; for what are we?
        Your murmurings are not against us, but against the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Moses said to Aaron, \u201CSay to all the congregation of Israel,
        \u2018Approach the Lord, because He has heard your murmurings.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So it happened that as Aaron spoke to the whole congregation of Israel,
        they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, the glory and brilliance of
        the Lord appeared in the cloud! '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI have heard the murmurings of the Israelites; speak to them,
        saying, \u2018At twilight you shall eat meat, and in the morning you shall
        be filled with bread; and you shall know that I am the Lord your God.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So in the evening the quails came up and covered the camp, and in
        the morning there was a blanket of dew around the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When the layer of dew evaporated, on the surface of the wilderness
        there was a fine, flake-like thing, as fine as frost on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "When the Israelites saw it, they said to one another, \u201CWhat
        is it?\u201D For they did not know what it was. And Moses said to them, \u201CThis
        is the bread which the Lord has given you to eat. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "This is what the Lord has commanded: \u2018Let every man gather as
        much of it as he needs. Take an omer for each person, according to the number
        of people each of you has in his tent.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The Israelites did so, and some gathered much [of it] and some [only
        a] little. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When they measured it with an omer, he who had gathered a large amount
        had no excess, and he who had gathered little had no lack; every man gathered
        according to his need (family size). '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Moses said, \u201CLet none of it be left [overnight] until [the next]
        morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But they did not listen to Moses, and some left a supply of it until
        morning, and it bred worms and became foul and rotten; and Moses was angry
        with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Sabbath Observed'
      title: The Sabbath Observed
      number: 21
      content: 'So they gathered it every morning, each as much as he needed, because
        when the sun was hot it melted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now on the sixth day they gathered twice as much bread, two omers
        for each person; and all the leaders of the congregation came and told Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He said to them, \u201CThis is what the Lord has said: \u2018Tomorrow
        is a solemn rest, a holy Sabbath to the Lord\u2019; bake and boil what you
        will bake and boil [today], and all that remains left over put aside for
        yourselves to keep until morning.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They put it aside until morning, as Moses told them, and it did not
        become foul nor was it wormy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CEat that today, for today is a Sabbath to
        the Lord; today you will not find it in the field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Six days you shall gather it, but on the seventh day, the Sabbath,
        there will be none [in the field].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now on the seventh day some of the people went out to gather, but
        they found none. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CHow long do you [people] refuse
        to keep My commandments and My instructions (laws)? "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "See, the Lord has given you the Sabbath; therefore He gives you the
        bread for two days on the sixth day. Let every man stay in his place; no
        man is to leave his place on the seventh day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So the people rested on the seventh day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The house of Israel called the bread manna; it was like coriander
        seed, white, and it tasted like flat pastry (wafers) made with honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CThis is the word which the Lord commands,
        \u2018Let an omer of it be kept throughout your generations, that they may
        see the bread with which I fed you in the wilderness, when I brought you
        out of the land of Egypt.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So Moses said to Aaron, \u201CTake a pot and put an omer of manna
        in it, and place it before the Lord to be kept throughout your generations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'As the Lord commanded Moses, so Aaron [eventually] placed it in the
        presence of the Testimony, to be kept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The Israelites ate manna forty years, until they reached an inhabited
        land; they ate the manna until they came to the border of the land of Canaan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: (Now an omer is the tenth of an ephah.)
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Water in the Rock'
      title: Water in the Rock
      number: 1
      content: '  Then all the congregation of the children of Israel moved on from
        the Wilderness of Sin by stages, according to the commandment of the Lord,
        and camped at Rephidim, but there was no water for the people to drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore the people quarreled with Moses and said, \u201CGive us
        water so we may [have something to] drink.\u201D And Moses said to them,
        \u201CWhy do you quarrel with me? Why do you tempt the Lord  and try His
        patience?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But the people were thirsty for water; and the people murmured against
        Moses and said, \u201CWhy did you bring us up from Egypt to kill us and our
        children and our livestock with thirst?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So Moses cried out to the Lord for help, saying, \u201CWhat shall
        I do with this people? They are almost ready to stone me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CPass before the people and take
        with you some of the elders of Israel; and take in your hand the staff with
        which you struck the Nile, and go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Behold, I will stand before you there on the rock at Horeb; there
        you shall strike the rock, and water will come out of it, so that the people
        may [have something to] drink.\u201D And Moses did so in the sight of the
        elders of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Amalek Fought'
      title: Amalek Fought
      number: 7
      content: "He named the place [where this miracle occurred] Massah (test) and
        Meribah (contention) because of the quarreling of the sons of Israel, and
        because they tested the [patience of the] Lord, saying, \u201CIs the Lord
        among us, or not?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then Amalek [and his people] came and fought with Israel at Rephidim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Moses said to Joshua, \u201CChoose men for us and go out, fight
        against Amalek [and his people]. Tomorrow I will stand on the top of the
        hill with the staff of God in my hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Joshua did as Moses said, and fought with Amalek; and Moses, Aaron,
        and Hur went up to the hilltop. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now when Moses held up his hand, Israel prevailed, and when he lowered
        his hand [due to fatigue], Amalek prevailed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Moses\u2019 hands were heavy and he grew tired. So they took
        a stone and put it under him, and he sat on it. Then Aaron and Hur held up
        his hands, one on one side and one on the other side; so it was that his
        hands were steady until the sun set. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Joshua overwhelmed and defeated Amalek and his people with the
        edge of the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CWrite this in the book as a memorial
        and recite it to Joshua, that I will utterly wipe out the memory of Amalek
        [and his people] from under heaven.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Moses built an altar and named it The Lord Is My Banner; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "saying, \u201CThe Lord has sworn [an oath]; the Lord will have war
        against [the people of] Amalek from generation to generation.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jethro, Moses\u2019 Father-in-law"
      title: "Jethro, Moses\u2019 Father-in-law"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Jethro (Reuel), the priest of Midian, Moses\u2019 father-in-law,
        heard of all that God had done for Moses and for Israel His people, and that
        the Lord had brought Israel out of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Jethro, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, took Moses\u2019 wife Zipporah,
        after he had sent her away [from Egypt], "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "along with her two sons, of whom one was named Gershom (stranger),
        for Moses said, \u201CI have been a stranger in a foreign land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The other [son] was named Eliezer (my God is help), for Moses said,
        \u201CThe God of my father was my help, and He rescued me from the sword
        of Pharaoh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jethro, his father-in-law, came with Moses\u2019 sons and his
        wife to [join] Moses in the wilderness where he was camped, at the mountain
        of God [that is, Mt. Sinai in Horeb]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He sent a message to Moses, \u201CI, your father-in-law Jethro, am
        coming to you with your wife and her two sons [who are] with her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Moses went out to meet his father-in-law, and he bowed down [in
        respect] and kissed him. They asked each other about their well-being and
        went into the tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Moses told his father-in-law about all that the Lord had done to
        Pharaoh and the Egyptians for Israel\u2019s sake, and about all the hardship
        that had happened during the journey, and how the Lord had rescued them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Jethro rejoiced over all the good things the Lord had done to Israel,
        in that He had rescued them from the hand of the Egyptians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jethro said, \u201CBlessed be the Lord, who has rescued you from
        the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand of Pharaoh, and who has rescued
        the people from under the hand of the Egyptians. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now I know that the Lord is greater than all gods; indeed, it was
        proven when they acted insolently toward Israel [and the Lord showed Himself
        infinitely superior to all their gods].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jethro, Moses\u2019 father-in-law, took a burnt offering and
        [other] sacrifices [to offer] to God, and Aaron came with all the elders
        of Israel to eat a meal with Moses\u2019 father-in-law before God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now the next day Moses sat to judge [the disputes] the people [had
        with one another], and the people stood around Moses from dawn to dusk. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "When Moses\u2019 father-in-law saw everything that he was doing for
        the people, he said, \u201CWhat is this that you are doing for the people?
        Why are you sitting alone [as a judge] with all the people standing around
        you from dawn to dusk?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Moses said to his father-in-law, \u201CBecause the people come to
        me to ask [about the will] of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Jethro Counsels Moses'
      title: Jethro Counsels Moses
      number: 16
      content: "When they have a dispute they come to me, and I judge between a man
        and his neighbor and I make known the statutes of God and His laws.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Moses\u2019 father-in-law said to him, \u201CThe thing that you are
        doing is not good. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You will certainly wear out both yourself and these people who are
        with you, because the task is too heavy for you [to bear]; you cannot do
        it alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now listen to me; I will advise you, and may God be with you [to
        confirm my advice]. You shall represent the people before God. You shall
        bring their disputes and causes to Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You shall teach them the decrees and laws. You shall show them the
        way they are to live and the work they are to do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Furthermore, you shall select from all the people competent men who
        [reverently] fear God, men of truth, those who hate dishonest gain; you shall
        place these over the people as leaders of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties
        and of tens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They shall judge the people at all times; have them bring every major
        dispute to you, but let them judge every minor dispute themselves. So it
        will be easier for you, and they will bear the burden with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "If you will do this thing and God so commands you, then you will
        be able to endure [the responsibility], and all these people will also go
        [back] to their tents in peace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Moses listened to his father-in-law and did everything that he
        had said. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Moses chose able men from all Israel and made them heads over the
        people, leaders of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties and of tens [from the
        highest to the lowest judicial levels]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And they judged the people at all times; they would bring the difficult
        cases to Moses, but every minor dispute they judged and decided themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then Moses said goodbye to his father-in-law, and Jethro went back
        to his own land (Midian).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Moses on Sinai'
      title: Moses on Sinai
      number: 1
      content: '  In the third month after the children of Israel had left the land
        of Egypt, the very same day, they came into the Wilderness of Sinai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When they moved out from Rephidim, they came to the Wilderness of
        Sinai and they camped there; Israel camped at the base of the mountain [of
        Sinai]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Moses went up to God [on the mountain], and the Lord called to him
        from the mountain, saying, \u201CSay this to the house of Jacob and tell
        the Israelites: "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018You have seen what I did to the Egyptians, and how I carried
        you on eagles\u2019 wings, and brought you to Myself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now therefore, if you will in fact obey My voice and keep My covenant
        (agreement), then you shall be My own special possession and treasure from
        among all peoples [of the world], for all the earth is Mine; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and you shall be to Me a kingdom of priests and a holy nation [set
        apart for My purpose].\u2019 These are the words that you shall speak to
        the Israelites.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Moses called for the elders of the people, and told them all these
        words which the Lord commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "All the people answered together and said, \u201CWe will do everything
        that the Lord has spoken.\u201D And Moses reported the words of the people
        to the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Lord said to Moses, \u201CBehold, I will come to you in a thick
        cloud, so that the people may hear when I speak with you and may believe
        and trust in you forever.\u201D Then Moses repeated the words of the people
        to the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The Lord also said to Moses, \u201CGo to the people and consecrate
        them today and tomorrow [that is, prepare them for My sacred purpose], and
        have them wash their clothes "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and be ready by the third day, because on the third day the Lord
        will come down on Mount Sinai [in the cloud] in the sight of all the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You shall set barriers for the people all around [the mountain],
        saying, \u2018Beware that you do not go up on the mountain or touch its border;
        whoever touches the mountain must be put to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "No hand shall touch him [that is, no one shall try to save the guilty
        party], but the offender must be stoned or shot through [with arrows]; whether
        man or animal [that touches the mountain], he shall not live.\u2019 When
        the ram\u2019s horn sounds a long blast, they shall come up to the mountain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Moses went down from the mountain to the people and sanctified
        them [for God\u2019s sacred purpose], and they washed their clothes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said to the people, \u201CBe prepared for the third day; do not
        be intimate with a woman.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So it happened on the third day, when it was morning, that there
        were thunder and flashes of lightning, and a thick cloud was on the mountain,
        and a very loud blast was sounded on a ram\u2019s horn, so that all the people
        who were in the camp trembled. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Lord Visits Sinai'
      title: The Lord Visits Sinai
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Moses brought the people out of the camp to meet God, and they
        stood and presented themselves at the foot of the mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Mount Sinai was wrapped in smoke because the Lord descended upon
        it in fire; its smoke ascended like the smoke of a furnace, and the whole
        mountain quaked violently. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And it happened, as the blast of the ram\u2019s horn grew louder
        and louder, Moses spoke and God answered him with [a voice of] thunder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The Lord came down on Mount Sinai, to the top of the mountain; and
        the Lord called Moses to the top of the mountain, and he went up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the Lord spoke to Moses, \u201CGo down, warn the people, so
        that they do not break through [the barriers around the mountain] to the
        Lord to see [Me], and many of them perish [as a result]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Also have the priests who approach the Lord consecrate (sanctify,
        set apart) themselves [for My sacred purpose], or else the Lord will break
        forth [in judgment] against them [and destroy them].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Moses said to the Lord, \u201CThe people cannot come up to Mount
        Sinai, because You warned us, saying, \u2018Set barriers around the mountain
        and consecrate it.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then the Lord said to him, \u201CGo down and come up again, you and
        Aaron with you; but do not let the priests and the people break through [the
        barriers] to come up to the Lord, or He will break forth [in judgment] against
        them [and destroy them].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So Moses went down to the people and told them [again about God\u2019s
        warning]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ten Commandments'
      title: The Ten Commandments
      number: 1
      content: '  Then God spoke all these words:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI am the Lord your God, who has brought you out of the land
        of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou shall have no other gods before Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYou shall not make for yourself any idol, or any likeness (form,
        manifestation) of what is in heaven above or on the earth beneath or in the
        water under the earth [as an object to worship]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall not worship them nor serve them; for I, the Lord your God,
        am a jealous (impassioned) God [demanding what is rightfully and uniquely
        mine], visiting (avenging) the iniquity (sin, guilt) of the fathers on the
        children [that is, calling the children to account for the sins of their
        fathers], to the third and fourth generations of those who hate Me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'but showing graciousness and steadfast lovingkindness to thousands
        [of generations] of those who love Me and keep My commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CYou shall not take the name of the Lord your God in vain [that
        is, irreverently, in false affirmations or in ways that impugn the character
        of God]; for the Lord will not hold guiltless nor leave unpunished the one
        who takes His name in vain [disregarding its reverence and its power].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CRemember the Sabbath (seventh) day to keep it holy (set apart,
        dedicated to God). "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Six days you shall labor and do all your work, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but the seventh day is a Sabbath [a day of rest dedicated] to the
        Lord your God; on that day you shall not do any work, you or your son, or
        your daughter, or your male servant, or your female servant, or your livestock
        or the temporary resident (foreigner) who stays within your [city] gates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For in six days the Lord made the heavens and the earth, the sea
        and everything that is in them, and He rested (ceased) on the seventh day.
        That is why the Lord blessed the Sabbath day and made it holy [that is, set
        it apart for His purposes].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHonor (respect, obey, care for) your father and your mother,
        so that your days may be prolonged in the land the Lord your God gives you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou shall not commit murder (unjustified, deliberate homicide).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CYou shall not commit adultery.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CYou shall not steal [secretly, openly, fraudulently, or through
        carelessness].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CYou shall not testify falsely [that is, lie, withhold, or manipulate
        the truth] against your neighbor (any person).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYou shall not covet [that is, selfishly desire and attempt
        to acquire] your neighbor\u2019s house; you shall not covet your neighbor\u2019s
        wife, or his male servant, or his female servant, or his ox, or his donkey,
        or anything that belongs to your neighbor.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now all the people witnessed the thunder and the flashes of lightning
        and the sound of the trumpet and the smoking mountain; and as they looked,
        the people were afraid, and they trembled [and moved backward] and stood
        at a [safe] distance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then they said to Moses, \u201CYou speak to us and we will listen,
        but do not let God speak to us or we will die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Moses said to the people, \u201CDo not be afraid; for God has come
        in order to test you, and in order that the fear of Him [that is, a profound
        reverence for Him] will remain with you, so that you do not sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So the people stood at a [safe] distance, but Moses approached the
        thick cloud where God was.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CThus you shall say to the Israelites,
        \u2018You have seen for yourselves that I have spoken to you from heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You shall not make other gods [to worship] besides Me; gods of silver
        or gods of gold, you shall not make [these lifeless idols] for yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall make an altar of earth for Me, and sacrifice on it your
        burnt offerings and your peace offerings, your sheep and your oxen. In every
        place where I cause My Name to be recorded and remembered [through revelation
        of My divine nature] I will come to you and bless you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'If you make an altar of stone for Me, you shall not build it of cut
        stones, for if you use a chisel on it, you will profane it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Nor shall you go up to My altar on steps, so that your nakedness
        will not be exposed on it.\u2019"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ordinances for the People'
      title: Ordinances for the People
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow these are the ordinances (laws) which you shall set before
        the Israelites:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf you purchase a Hebrew servant [because of his debt or poverty],
        he shall serve six years, and in the seventh [year] he shall leave as a free
        man, paying nothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If he came [to you] alone, he shall leave alone; if he came married,
        then his wife shall leave with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If his master gives him a wife, and she gives birth to sons or daughters,
        the wife and her children shall belong to her master, and he shall leave
        [your service] alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if the servant plainly says, \u2018I love my master, my wife
        and my children; I will not leave as a free man,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "then his master shall bring him to God [that is, to the judges who
        act in God\u2019s name], then he shall bring him to the door or doorpost.
        And his master shall pierce his ear with an awl (strong needle); and he shall
        serve him for life.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIf a man sells his daughter to be a female servant, she shall
        not go free [after six years] as male servants do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'If she does not please her master who has chosen her for himself
        [as a wife], he shall let her be redeemed [by her family]. He does not have
        the authority to sell her to a foreign people, because he has been unfair
        to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If her master chooses her [as a wife] for his son, he shall act toward
        her as if she were legally his daughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If her master marries another wife, he may not reduce her food, her
        clothing, or her privilege as a wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Personal Injuries'
      title: Personal Injuries
      number: 11
      content: 'If he does not do these three things for her, then shall she leave
        free, without payment of money.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhoever strikes a man so that he dies must be put to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'However, if he did not lie in wait [for him], but God allowed him
        to fall into his hand, then I will establish for you a place to which he
        may escape [for protection until duly tried]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But if a man acts intentionally against another and kills him by
        [design through] treachery, you are to take him from My altar [to which he
        may have fled for protection], so that he may be put to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhoever strikes his father or his mother must be put to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWhoever kidnaps a man, whether he sells him or is found with
        him in his possession, must be put to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CWhoever curses his father or his mother or treats them contemptuously
        must be put to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CIf men quarrel and one strikes another with a stone or with
        his fist, and he does not die but is confined to bed, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'if he gets up and walks around leaning on his cane, then the one
        who struck him shall be left [physically] unpunished; he must only pay for
        his loss of time [at work], and the costs [of treatment and recuperation]
        until he is thoroughly healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CIf a man strikes his male or his female servant with a staff
        and the servant dies at his hand, he must be punished. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'If, however, the servant survives for a day or two, the offender
        shall not be punished, for the [injured] servant is his own property.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIf men fight with each other and injure a pregnant woman so
        that she gives birth prematurely [and the baby lives], yet there is no further
        injury, the one who hurt her must be punished with a fine [paid] to the woman\u2019s
        husband, as much as the judges decide. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But if there is any further injury, then you shall require [as a
        penalty] life for life, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'burn for burn, wound for wound, bruise for bruise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CIf a man hits the eye of his male servant or female servant
        and it is destroyed, he must let the servant go free because of [the loss
        of] the eye. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And if he knocks out the tooth of his male servant or female servant,
        he must let the servant go free because of [the loss of] the tooth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CIf an ox gores a man or a woman to death, the ox must be stoned
        and its meat shall not be eaten; but the owner of the ox shall be cleared
        [of responsibility]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'But if the ox has tried to gore on a previous occasion, and its owner
        has been warned, but has not kept it confined and it kills a man or a woman,
        the ox shall be stoned and its owner shall be put to death as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'If a ransom is demanded of him [in return for his life], then he
        shall give whatever is demanded for the redemption of his life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "If the ox has gored another\u2019s son or daughter, he shall be dealt
        with according to this same rule. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "If the ox gores a male or a female servant, the owner shall give
        to the servant\u2019s master thirty shekels of silver [the purchase price
        for a slave], and the ox shall be stoned.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CIf a man leaves a pit open, or digs a pit and does not cover
        it, and an ox or a donkey falls into it, "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "the owner of the pit shall make restitution; he shall give money
        to the animal\u2019s owner, but the dead [animal] shall be his.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CIf one man\u2019s ox injures another\u2019s so that it dies,
        then they shall sell the live ox and divide the proceeds equally; they shall
        also divide the dead ox [between them]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Or if it is known that the ox was previously in the habit of goring,
        and its owner has not kept it confined, he must make restitution of ox for
        ox, and the dead [animal] shall be his.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Property Rights'
      title: Property Rights
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CIf a man steals an ox or sheep and kills or sells it, he
        shall make restitution of five oxen for an ox or four sheep for a sheep.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CIf a thief is caught breaking in [after dark] and is struck
        [by the owner] so that he dies, there shall be no bloodguilt for him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But if the sun has risen, there will be bloodguilt for him. The thief
        [if he lives] must make [full] restitution; if he has nothing, then he shall
        be sold [as a slave to make restitution] for his theft. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If the animal that he stole is found alive in his possession, whether
        it is ox or donkey or sheep, he shall pay double [for it].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CIf a man causes a field or vineyard to be grazed bare or lets
        his livestock loose so that it grazes in another man\u2019s field, he shall
        make restitution from the best of his own field and the best of his own vineyard.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CIf fire breaks out and spreads to thorn bushes so that the
        stacked grain or standing grain or the field is consumed, he who started
        the fire shall make full restitution.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CIf a man gives his neighbor money or [other] goods to keep
        [for him while he is away] and it is stolen from the neighbor\u2019s house,
        then, if the thief is caught, he shall pay double [for it]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "If the thief is not caught, the owner of the house shall appear before
        the judges [who act in God\u2019s name], to determine whether or not he had
        stolen his neighbor\u2019s goods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For every offense involving property, whether it concerns ox, donkey,
        sheep, clothing, or any piece of lost property, which another identifies
        as his, the case of both parties shall come before the judges [who act in
        God\u2019s name]. Whomever the judges pronounce guilty shall pay double to
        his neighbor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CIf a man gives his neighbor a donkey or an ox or a sheep or
        any [other] animal to keep [for him], and it dies or is injured or taken
        away while no one is looking, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "then an oath before the Lord shall be made by the two of them that
        he has not taken his neighbor\u2019s property; and the owner of it shall
        accept his word and not require him to make restitution. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But if it is actually stolen from him [when in his care], he shall
        make restitution to its owner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If it is torn to pieces [by some predator or by accident], let him
        bring the mangled carcass as evidence; he shall not make restitution for
        what was torn to pieces.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAnd if a man borrows an animal from his neighbor, and it gets
        injured or dies while its owner is not with it, the borrower shall make full
        restitution. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Various Laws'
      title: Various Laws
      number: 15
      content: 'But if the owner is with it [when the damage is done], the borrower
        shall not make restitution. If it was hired, the damage is included in [the
        price of] its fee.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CIf a man seduces a virgin who is not betrothed, and lies with
        her, he must pay a dowry (marriage price) for her to be his wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If her father absolutely refuses to give her to him, he must [still]
        pay money equivalent to the dowry of virgins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall not allow a woman who practices sorcery to live.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CWhoever lies with an animal must be put to death.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CHe who sacrifices to any god, other than to the Lord alone,
        shall be put under a ban (designated) for destruction (execution).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYou shall not wrong a stranger or oppress him, for you were
        strangers in the land of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You shall not harm or oppress any widow or fatherless child. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If you harm or oppress them in any way, and they cry at all to Me
        [for help], I will most certainly hear their cry; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and My wrath shall be kindled and burn; I will kill you with the
        sword, and your wives shall become widows and your children fatherless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CIf you lend money to any one of My people with you who is poor,
        you shall not act as a creditor (professional moneylender) to him; you shall
        not charge him interest. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "If you ever take your [poor] neighbor\u2019s robe in pledge, you
        must return it to him before sunset, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'for that is his only covering; it is his clothing for his body. In
        what shall he sleep? And when he cries to Me [for help], I will hear him,
        for I am compassionate and gracious.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CYou shall not curse God, nor curse the ruler of your people
        [since he administers God\u2019s law].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CYou shall not delay the offering from your harvest and your
        vintage. You shall give (consecrate, dedicate) to Me the firstborn of your
        sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'You shall do the same with your oxen and with your sheep. It shall
        be with its mother for seven days; on the eighth day you shall give it [as
        an offering] to Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou shall be holy men to Me; therefore you shall not eat meat
        [from any animal] that has been torn to pieces [by predators] in the field;
        you shall throw it to the dogs."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Various Laws'
      title: Various Laws
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CYou shall not give a false report; you shall not join hands
        with the wicked to be a malicious witness [promoting wrong and violence]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You shall not follow a crowd to do [something] evil, nor shall you
        testify at a trial or in a dispute so as to side with a crowd in order to
        pervert justice;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'nor shall you favor or be partial to a poor man in his dispute [simply
        because he is poor].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CIf you meet your enemy\u2019s ox or his donkey wandering off,
        you must bring it back to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If you see the donkey of one who hates you lying helpless under its
        load, you shall not leave the man to deal with it [alone]; you must help
        him release the animal [from its burden].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CYou shall not pervert (bend) the justice due to your poor in
        his dispute. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Keep far away from a false charge or action, and do not condemn to
        death the innocent or the righteous, for I will not justify and acquit the
        guilty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CYou shall not accept a bribe, for a bribe blinds the clear-sighted
        and subverts the testimony and the cause of the righteous.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Sabbath and Land'
      title: The Sabbath and Land
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou shall not oppress a stranger, for you know the soul [the
        feelings, thoughts, and concerns] of a stranger, for you were strangers in
        Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou shall sow your land six years and harvest its yield, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'but the seventh year you shall let it rest and lie uncultivated,
        so that the poor among your people may eat [what the land grows naturally];
        whatever they leave the animals of the field may eat. You shall do the same
        with your vineyard and olive grove.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CSix days [each week] you shall do your work, but on the seventh
        day you shall stop [working] so that your ox and your donkey may settle down
        and rest, and the son of your female servant, as well as your stranger, may
        be refreshed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Three National Feasts'
      title: Three National Feasts
      number: 13
      content: 'Now concerning everything which I have said to you, be on your guard;
        do not mention the name of other gods [either in a blessing or in a curse];
        do not let such speech be heard [coming] from your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CThree times a year you shall celebrate a feast [dedicated]
        to Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You shall observe the Feast of Unleavened Bread; for seven days you
        shall eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, at the appointed time in
        the month of Abib, for in it you came out of Egypt. No one shall appear before
        Me empty-handed [but you shall bring sacrificial offerings]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Also [you shall observe] the Feast of Harvest (Weeks, Pentecost,
        or First Fruits), acknowledging the first fruits of your labor, of what you
        sow in the field. And [third] the Feast of Ingathering (Booths or Tabernacles)
        at the end of the year when you gather in [the fruit of] your labors from
        the field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Three times a year all your males shall appear before the Lord God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leavened
        bread; and the fat of My feast is not to be left overnight until morning.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Conquest of the Land'
      title: Conquest of the Land
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CYou shall bring the choice first fruits of your ground into
        the house of the Lord your God.\u201CYou shall not boil a young goat in its
        mother\u2019s milk.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am going to send an Angel before you to keep and
        guard you on the way and to bring you to the place I have prepared. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Be on your guard before Him, listen to and obey His voice; do not
        be rebellious toward Him or provoke Him, for He will not pardon your transgression,
        since My Name (authority) is in Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But if you will indeed listen to and truly obey His voice and do
        everything that I say, then I will be an enemy to your enemies and an adversary
        to your adversaries. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When My Angel goes before you and brings you to [the land of] the
        Amorite, the Hittite, the Perizzite, the Canaanite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite,
        I will reject them and completely destroy them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall not bow down to worship their gods, nor serve them, nor
        do [anything] in accordance with their practices. You shall completely overthrow
        them and break down their [sacred] pillars and images [of pagan worship]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall serve [only] the Lord your God, and He shall bless your
        bread and water. I will also remove sickness from among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'No one shall suffer miscarriage or be barren in your land; I will
        fulfill the number of your days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'I will send My terror ahead of you, and I will throw into confusion
        all the people among whom you come, and I will make all your enemies turn
        their backs to you [in flight]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'I will send hornets ahead of you which shall drive out the Hivite,
        the Canaanite, and the Hittite before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'I will not drive them out before you in a single year, so that the
        land does not become desolate [due to lack of attention] and the [wild] animals
        of the field do not become too numerous for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I will drive them out before you little by little, until you have
        increased and are strong enough to take possession of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'I will establish your borders from the Red Sea to the Sea of the
        Philistines (the Mediterranean), and from the wilderness to the River Euphrates;
        for I will hand over the residents of the land to you, and you shall drive
        them out before you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'You shall not make a covenant with them or with their gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "They shall not live in your land, because they will make you sin
        against Me; for if you serve their gods, it is certain to be a trap for you
        [resulting in judgment].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: People Affirm Their Covenant with God'
      title: People Affirm Their Covenant with God
      number: 1
      content: "  Then God said to Moses, \u201CCome up to the Lord, you and Aaron,
        Nadab and Abihu (Aaron\u2019s older sons), and seventy of Israel\u2019s elders,
        and you shall worship at a [safe] distance. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Moses alone shall approach the Lord, but the others shall not come
        near, nor shall the people come up with him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Moses came and told the people everything that the Lord had
        said and all the ordinances. And all the people answered with one voice,
        \u201CEverything the Lord has said we will do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moses wrote down all the words of the Lord. Then he got up early
        in the morning, and built an altar [for worship] at the foot of the mountain
        with twelve pillars (memorial stones) representing the twelve tribes of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then he sent young Israelite men, and they offered burnt offerings
        and sacrificed young bulls as peace offerings to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Moses took half of the blood and put it in large basins, and [the
        other] half of the blood he sprinkled on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he took the Book of the Covenant and read it aloud to the people;
        and they said, \u201CEverything that the Lord has said we will do, and we
        will be obedient.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So Moses took the blood [which had been placed in the large basins]
        and sprinkled it on the people, and said, \u201CBehold the blood of the covenant,
        which the Lord has made with you in accordance with all these words.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Moses, Aaron, Nadab, and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of
        Israel went up [the mountainside], '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and they saw [a manifestation of] the God of Israel; and under His
        feet there appeared to be a pavement of sapphire, just as clear as the sky
        itself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Yet He did not stretch out His hand against the nobles of the Israelites;
        and they saw [the manifestation of the presence of] God, and ate and drank.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now the Lord said to Moses, \u201CCome up to Me on the mountain and
        stay there, and I will give you the stone tablets with the law and the commandments
        which I have written for their instruction.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Moses arose with Joshua his attendant, and he went up to the mountain
        of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he said to the elders, \u201CWait here for us until we come back
        to you. Remember that Aaron and Hur are with you; whoever has a legal matter,
        let him go to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Moses went up to the mountain, and the cloud covered the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The glory and brilliance of the Lord rested on Mount Sinai, and the
        cloud covered it for six days. On the seventh day God called to Moses from
        the midst of the cloud. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the sight of the Israelites the appearance of the glory and brilliance
        of the Lord was like consuming fire on the top of the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Moses entered the midst of the cloud and went up the mountain; and
        he was on the mountain forty days and forty nights.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Offerings for the Sanctuary'
      title: Offerings for the Sanctuary
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTell the children of Israel to take an offering for Me. From
        every man whose heart moves him [to give willingly] you shall take My offering. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'This is the offering you are to receive from them: gold, silver,
        and bronze, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "blue, purple, and scarlet fabric, fine twisted linen, goats\u2019
        hair,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "rams\u2019 skins dyed red, porpoise skins, acacia wood, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '[olive] oil for lighting, balsam for the anointing oil and for the
        fragrant incense, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "onyx stones and setting stones for the [priest\u2019s] ephod and
        for the breastpiece. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Have them build a sanctuary for Me, so that I may dwell among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Ark of the Covenant'
      title: Ark of the Covenant
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall construct it in accordance with everything that I am going
        to show you, as the pattern of the tabernacle and the pattern of all its
        furniture.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThey shall make an ark of acacia wood two and a half cubits
        long, one and a half cubits wide, and one and a half cubits high. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall overlay the ark with pure gold, overlay it inside and out,
        and you shall make a gold border (frame) around its top. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You shall cast four gold rings for it and attach them to the four
        feet, two rings on either side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall make [carrying] poles of acacia wood and overlay them with
        gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and put the poles through the rings on the sides of the ark, by which
        to carry it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The poles shall remain in the rings of the ark; they shall not be
        removed from it [so that the ark itself need not be touched]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You shall put into the ark the Testimony (Ten Commandments) which
        I will give you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CYou shall make a mercy seat (cover) of pure gold, two and a
        half cubits long and one and a half cubits wide. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You shall make two cherubim (winged angelic figures) of [solid] hammered
        gold at the two ends of the mercy seat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Make one cherub at each end, making the cherubim of one piece with
        the mercy seat at its two ends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The cherubim shall have their wings spread upward, covering the mercy
        seat with their wings and facing each other. The faces of the cherubim are
        to be looking downward toward the mercy seat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'You shall put the mercy seat on the top of the ark, and in the ark
        you shall put the Testimony which I will give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: The Table of Bread'
      title: The Table of Bread
      number: 22
      content: 'There I will meet with you; from above the mercy seat, from between
        the two cherubim which are on the ark of the Testimony, I will speak [intimately]
        with you regarding every commandment that I will give you for the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CYou shall make a table of acacia wood, two cubits long, one
        cubit wide, and one and a half cubits high. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall overlay it with pure gold and make a border of gold around
        the top of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall make a rim of a hand width around it; you shall make a
        gold border for the rim around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "You shall make four gold rings for it and fasten them at the four
        corners that are on the table\u2019s four legs. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The rings shall be close against the rim as holders for the poles
        to carry the table. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'You shall make the poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold,
        so that the table may be carried with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You shall make its plates [for the showbread] and its cups [for incense]
        and its pitchers and bowls for sacrificial drink offerings; you shall make
        them of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Golden Lampstand'
      title: The Golden Lampstand
      number: 30
      content: 'You shall set the bread of the Presence (showbread) on the table
        before Me at all times.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou shall make a lampstand of pure gold. The lampstand and
        its base and its shaft shall be made of hammered work; its cups, its calyxes
        and its flowers shall be all of one piece with it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Six branches shall come out of its sides; three branches of the lampstand
        out of the one side and three branches of the lampstand out of its other
        side [the shaft being the seventh branch]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Three cups shall be made like almond blossoms, each with a calyx
        and a flower on one branch, and three cups made like almond blossoms on the
        other branch with a calyx and a flower\u2014so for the six branches coming
        out of the lampstand; "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'and in the [center shaft of the] lampstand [you shall make] four
        cups shaped like almond blossoms, with their calyxes and their flowers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'A calyx shall be under the first pair of branches coming out of it,
        and a calyx under the second pair of branches coming out of it, and a calyx
        under the third pair of branches coming out of it, for the six branches coming
        out of the lampstand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Their calyxes and their branches shall be of one piece with it; all
        of it shall be one piece of hammered work of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Then you shall make the lamps [of the lampstand] seven in number
        [with one lamp at the top of the shaft]. The priests shall set up its seven
        lamps so that they will light the space in front of it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Its snuffers and their trays shall be of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'It shall be made from a talent (50-80 lbs.) of pure gold, including
        all these utensils. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: See that you make them [exactly] after their pattern which was shown
        to you on the mountain.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Curtains of Linen'
      title: Curtains of Linen
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CMoreover, you shall make the tabernacle (sacred tent of worship)
        with ten [interior] curtains of fine twisted linen, and blue, purple, and
        scarlet fabric; you shall make them with [embroidered] cherubim, the handwork
        of a skillful craftsman. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The length of each curtain shall be twenty-eight cubits, and the
        width of each curtain four cubits; all of the curtains shall measure the
        same. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The five curtains shall be joined to one another, and the other five
        curtains shall be joined to one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall make loops of blue on the outer edge of the last curtain
        in the first set, and likewise in the second set. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall make fifty loops on the one curtain, and fifty loops on
        the edge of the last curtain that is in the second set. The loops on one
        curtain correspond to the loops on the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Curtains of Goats\u2019 Hair"
      title: "Curtains of Goats\u2019 Hair"
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall make fifty gold hooks, and fasten the curtains together
        with the hooks; and the tabernacle shall be one unit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThen you shall make [exterior] curtains of goats\u2019 hair
        as a tent over the tabernacle. You shall make eleven curtains in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Each curtain shall be thirty cubits long and four cubits wide. The
        eleven curtains shall all measure the same. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall join five curtains by themselves and the other six curtains
        by themselves, and you shall double over the sixth curtain at the front of
        the tent [to make a closed door]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Make fifty loops on the edge of the outermost curtain in the first
        set, and fifty loops on the edge of the outermost curtain in the second set.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CYou shall make fifty bronze hooks and put the hooks into the
        loops and join the tent together so that it may be one unit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The overlapping part that is left over from the tent curtains, the
        half curtain that is left over, shall lap over the back of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The cubit on one side and the cubit on the other, of what is left
        over in the length of the curtains of the tent shall lap over the sides of
        the tabernacle on one side and the other side, to cover it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Boards and Sockets'
      title: Boards and Sockets
      number: 14
      content: "You shall make a third covering for the tent of rams\u2019 skins
        dyed red, and a fourth covering above that of porpoise skins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CThen you shall make the boards for the tabernacle of acacia
        wood, standing upright [as a trellis-like frame]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The length of each board shall be ten cubits and the width of each
        board shall be one and a half cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Make two dovetails in each board for fitting [them] together; you
        shall do the same for all the tabernacle boards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'You shall make the boards for the tabernacle [in the following quantities]:
        twenty boards for the south side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You shall make forty silver sockets under the twenty boards, two
        sockets under each board for its two dovetails, and two sockets under another
        board for its two dovetails; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'for the north side of the tabernacle there shall be twenty boards, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and their forty silver sockets, two sockets under each board. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the back or west side of the tabernacle you shall make six boards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Make two boards for the corners of the tabernacle at the rear [on
        both sides]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'They shall be joined together underneath, and joined together on
        top with one ring. So shall it be for both of them; they shall form the two
        [rear] corners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'There shall be eight boards and sixteen silver sockets; two sockets
        under each board.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThen you shall make [fifteen] bars of acacia wood: five for
        the boards of one side of the tabernacle, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and five bars for the boards of the other side of the tabernacle,
        and five bars for the boards of the rear end of the tabernacle, for the back
        wall toward the west. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the middle bar in the center of the boards shall pass through
        [horizontally] from end to end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You shall overlay the boards with gold and make their rings of gold
        to hold the bars. You shall overlay the bars with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Veil and Screen'
      title: The Veil and Screen
      number: 30
      content: 'You shall erect the tabernacle according to its plan [the direction
        corresponding to its meaning and purpose] which has been shown to you on
        the mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou shall make a veil [to divide the two rooms] of blue, purple,
        and scarlet fabric and fine twisted linen, skillfully worked with cherubim
        on it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'You shall hang it on four pillars (support poles) of acacia wood
        overlaid with gold, with gold hooks, on four silver sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'You shall hang the veil from the hooks [that connect the curtains
        together], and you shall bring the ark of the Testimony there within the
        veil. The veil shall separate for you the Holy Place and the Holy of Holies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You shall put the mercy seat on the ark of the Testimony in the Holy
        of Holies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'You shall set the table [for the bread] outside the veil [in the
        Holy Place] on the north side, and the lampstand opposite the table on the
        south side of the tabernacle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CYou shall make a screen [to provide a covering] for the doorway
        of the tent of blue, purple, and scarlet fabric and finely woven [embroidered]
        linen, the work of an embroiderer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: You shall make five pillars (support poles) of acacia wood to support
        the hanging curtain and overlay them with gold. Their hooks shall be of gold,
        and you shall cast five [base] sockets of bronze for them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Bronze Altar'
      title: The Bronze Altar
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CAnd you shall make the altar [for burnt offerings] of acacia
        wood, five cubits long and five cubits wide; the altar shall be square, and
        its height shall be three cubits. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Make horns (horn-shaped projections) for it on its four corners;
        the horns shall be of one piece with it, and you shall overlay it with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall make pots to remove its ashes, and shovels, basins [to
        catch the blood of the sacrificed animal], meat-forks, and firepans [to store
        live coals]. You shall make all its utensils of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Also make a grate for it, a network of bronze; and on the grid you
        are to make four bronze rings at its four corners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And you shall put it under the ledge of the altar, so that the grid
        will extend halfway up the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall make [carrying] poles for the altar, poles of acacia wood,
        overlaid with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The poles shall be inserted through the rings on the two sides of
        the altar so that it may be carried. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Court of the Tabernacle'
      title: Court of the Tabernacle
      number: 8
      content: 'You are to make the altar hollow with planks; as you were shown on
        the mountain [of Sinai], so shall it be made.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CYou shall make the court of the tabernacle. The south side
        of the court is to have curtains of fine twisted linen, a hundred cubits
        long for one side; "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'it shall have twenty pillars and twenty bronze sockets; but the hooks
        of the pillars and their fasteners shall be silver; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'likewise for the north side there shall be curtains, a hundred cubits
        long, and its twenty pillars and twenty bronze sockets; but the hooks of
        the pillars and their fasteners shall be silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the width of the court on the west side there shall be curtains
        of fifty cubits, with ten pillars (support poles) and ten sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The width of the court [to the front], on the east side shall be
        fifty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The curtains for one side [of the gate] shall be fifteen cubits with
        three pillars and three sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'On the other side [of the gate] the curtains shall be fifteen cubits
        with three pillars and three sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For the gate of the court there shall be a screen [to provide a covering]
        of twenty cubits, of blue, purple, and scarlet fabric and finely woven [embroidered]
        linen, the work of an embroiderer, with four pillars and four [base] sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All the pillars (support poles) around the court shall be joined
        together with silver rods; their hooks shall be of silver and their sockets
        of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The length of the court shall be a hundred cubits, and the width
        fifty [cubits] throughout, and the height five cubits of fine twisted linen,
        and their sockets of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "All the tabernacle\u2019s utensils and instruments used in all its
        service, and all its stakes, and all the stakes for the court, shall be of
        bronze.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CYou shall command the Israelites to provide you with clear
        oil of beaten olives for the light, to make a lamp burn continually [every
        night]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: In the Tent of Meeting [of God with His people], outside the veil
        which is in front of the [ark of the] Testimony [and sets it apart], Aaron
        [the high priest] and his sons shall keep the lamp burning from evening to
        morning before the Lord. It shall be a perpetual statute [to be observed]
        throughout their generations on behalf of the Israelites.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Garments of the Priests'
      title: Garments of the Priests
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CNow bring your brother Aaron near, and his sons with him
        from among the sons of Israel, so that he may serve as priest to Me\u2014Aaron,
        Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar, Aaron\u2019s sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You are to make sacred garments [official clothing reserved for holy
        services] for Aaron your brother, for honor and for beauty (ornamentation). '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Tell all the skilled and talented people whom I have endowed with
        a spirit of wisdom, that they are to make Aaron\u2019s garments to sanctify
        him and set him apart to serve as a priest for Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'These are the garments which they shall make: a breastpiece and an
        ephod [for the breastpiece] and a robe and a tunic of checkered work, a turban,
        and a sash. They shall make sacred garments for Aaron your brother and his
        sons, so that he may serve as a priest to Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They are to use the gold and the blue and the purple and the scarlet
        fabric and fine twisted linen [from the people],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and they shall make the ephod of gold and blue, purple, and scarlet
        fabric and fine twisted linen, skillfully woven and [beautifully] worked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It is to have two shoulder pieces joined to its two [back and front]
        ends, so that it may be joined together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the skillfully woven sash, which is on the ephod shall be made
        of the same material: of gold, of blue, purple, and scarlet fabric and fine
        twisted linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall take two onyx stones and engrave on them the names of the
        [twelve] sons of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'six of their names on one stone and the remaining six names on the
        other stone, arranged in the order of their births. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'With the work of a jeweler, like the engravings of a signet, you
        shall engrave the two stones according to the names of the sons of Israel.
        You shall have them set in filigree [settings] of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You shall put the two stones on the [two] shoulder pieces of the
        ephod [of the high priest], as memorial stones for Israel; and Aaron shall
        bear their names on his two shoulders as a memorial before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall make filigree [settings] of gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and you are to make two chains of pure gold like twisted cords, and
        fasten the corded chains to the settings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CYou are to make a breastpiece of judgment, the work of a skilled
        and talented craftsman; like the work of the ephod you shall make it: of
        gold, of blue, purple, and scarlet fabric and of fine twisted linen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The breastpiece shall be square and folded double; a span [about
        nine inches] in length and a span in width. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You shall mount on it four rows of stones: the first row shall be
        a row of ruby, topaz, and emerald; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the second row a turquoise, a sapphire, and a diamond; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the third row a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and the fourth row a beryl and an onyx and a jasper; they shall be
        set in gold filigree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The [engraved] stones shall be twelve, according to the names of
        [the twelve tribes of] the sons of Israel; they shall be like the engravings
        of a signet, each with its name for the twelve tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You shall make for the breastpiece chains of pure gold twisted like
        cords. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You shall make on the breastpiece two rings of gold, and shall put
        the two rings on the two ends of the breastpiece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You shall put the two twisted cords of gold in the two rings which
        are on the ends of the breastpiece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The other two ends of the two cords you shall fasten in the two filigree
        settings in front, putting them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You shall make two gold rings and put them at the two ends of the
        breastpiece, on its inside edge next to the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'You are to make two gold rings and attach them to the lower part
        of the two shoulder pieces of the ephod in front, close to the place where
        it is joined, above the skillfully woven sash of the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'They shall bind the breastpiece by its rings to the rings of the
        ephod with a blue cord, so that it will be above the skillfully woven sash
        of the ephod, so that the breastpiece will not come loose from the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So Aaron shall carry the names of the sons of Israel (Jacob) in the
        breastpiece of judgment over his heart when he enters the Holy Place, to
        bring them in continual remembrance before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "In the breastpiece of judgment you shall put the Urim (Lights) and
        the Thummim (Perfections) [to be used for determining God\u2019s will in
        a matter]. They shall be over Aaron\u2019s heart whenever he goes before
        the Lord, and Aaron shall always carry the judgment (verdict, judicial decisions)
        of the sons of Israel over his heart before the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall make the robe of the ephod all of blue. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'There shall be an opening at its top in the center [for the head],
        with a binding of woven work around the opening, like the opening in a coat
        of armor, so that it will not tear or fray. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'You shall make pomegranates of blue, purple, and scarlet fabric all
        around its hem, with gold bells between them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'a golden bell and a pomegranate, a golden bell and a pomegranate,
        all around the [bottom] hem of the robe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Aaron shall wear the robe when he ministers, and its sound shall
        be heard when he goes [alone] into the Holy Place before the Lord, and when
        he comes out, so that he will not die there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make a plate of pure gold and engrave on it,
        like the engravings of a signet, \u2018Holy to the Lord.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'You shall fasten it on the front of the turban with a blue cord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "It shall be on Aaron\u2019s forehead, and Aaron shall take away the
        guilt from the holy things which the sons of Israel dedicate, with regard
        to all their holy gifts. It shall always be on his forehead, so that they
        may be accepted before the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "\u201CYou shall weave the tunic of checkered work of fine linen,
        and make a turban of fine linen. You shall make a sash, the work of an embroiderer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CFor Aaron\u2019s sons you shall make tunics and sashes and
        [ornamental] caps, for glory and honor and beauty. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'You shall put the various articles of clothing on Aaron your brother
        and on his sons with him, and shall anoint them and ordain and sanctify them,
        so that they may serve Me as priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'You shall make for them [white] linen undergarments to cover their
        bare flesh, reaching from the waist to the thighs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: The various articles of clothing shall be on Aaron and on his sons
        when they enter the Tent of Meeting, or when they approach the altar [of
        incense] to minister in the Holy Place, so that they do not incur guilt and
        die. It shall be a statute forever to Aaron and to his descendants after
        him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Consecration of the Priests'
      title: Consecration of the Priests
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CThis is what you shall do to consecrate Aaron and his sons
        so that they may serve Me as priests: take one young bull and two rams, without
        blemish, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and unleavened bread and unleavened cakes mixed with oil, and unleavened
        wafers spread with oil; you shall make them of fine wheat flour. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall put them in one basket, and present them in the basket
        along with the bull and the two rams. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then bring Aaron and his sons to the doorway of the Tent of Meeting
        [out where the basin is] and wash them with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then you shall take the garments, and put on Aaron the tunic and
        the robe of the ephod and the ephod and the breastpiece, and wrap him with
        the skillfully woven sash of the ephod; '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and you shall put the turban on his head and put the holy crown on
        the turban. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then you shall take the anointing oil and pour it on his head and
        anoint him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You shall bring his sons and put tunics on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Sacrifices'
      title: The Sacrifices
      number: 9
      content: "And you shall wrap them with sashes, Aaron and his sons, and put
        the [ornamental] caps on them; and the priest\u2019s office shall be theirs
        by a perpetual statute. So you shall ordain Aaron and his sons.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThen you shall bring the bull before the Tent of Meeting, and
        Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the bull\u2019s head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then you shall kill the bull before the Lord by the doorway of the
        Tent of Meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And you shall take some of the blood of the bull and with your finger
        put it on the horns of the altar [of burnt offering], and you shall pour
        out the remainder of the blood at the base of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall take all the fat that covers the intestines and the lobe
        of the liver, and the two kidneys and the fat that is on them, and offer
        them up in smoke on the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the meat of the bull, its hide, and the contents of its intestines
        you shall burn in the fire outside the camp; it is a sin offering.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CAnd you shall take one of the rams, and Aaron and his sons
        shall lay their hands on the head of the ram; "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'then you shall kill the ram and you shall take its blood and sprinkle
        it around the altar [of burnt offering]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then you shall cut the ram into pieces, and wash its intestines and
        legs, and place them with its pieces and its head, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and you shall burn the whole ram on the altar. It is a burnt offering
        to the Lord: it is a sweet and soothing aroma, an offering by fire to the
        Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CThen you shall take the other ram, and Aaron and his sons shall
        lay their hands on the head of the ram. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then you shall kill the ram, and take some of its blood and put it
        on the tip of the right ears of Aaron and his sons and on the thumbs of their
        right hands and on the big toes of their right feet, and sprinkle the [rest
        of the] blood around on the altar [of burnt offering]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then you shall take some of the blood that is on the altar and some
        of the anointing oil, and sprinkle it on Aaron and his garments and on his
        sons and their garments. Now Aaron and his garments and his sons and their
        garments shall be consecrated (dedicated, made holy, declared sacred for
        God\u2019s purpose).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CYou shall also take the fat of the ram, the fat tail, the fat
        that covers the intestines, the lobe of the liver, the two kidneys with the
        fat that is on them, and the right thigh; (for it is a ram of ordination), "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and one loaf of bread and one cake of oiled bread and one wafer out
        of the basket of the unleavened bread that is before the Lord; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and you shall put all these in the hands of Aaron and his sons, and
        wave them as a wave offering before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then you shall take them from their hands, add them to the burnt
        offering, and burn them on the altar for a sweet and soothing aroma before
        the Lord; it is an offering by fire to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CThen you shall take the breast of the ram of Aaron\u2019s ordination,
        and wave it as a wave offering before the Lord; and it shall be your (Moses)
        portion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "You shall consecrate the waved breast offering [of the ram] used
        in the ordination and the waved thigh offering of the priests\u2019 portion,
        since it is [a contribution] for Aaron and for his sons. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'It shall be for Aaron and his sons as their due portion from the
        Israelites forever, for it is a heave offering. It shall be a heave offering
        to the Lord from the Israelites from the sacrifices of their peace offerings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CThe holy garments of Aaron shall be for his sons after him,
        to be anointed and ordained in them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Food of the Priests'
      title: Food of the Priests
      number: 30
      content: 'That son who is [high] priest in his place shall put them on [each
        day for] seven days when he comes into the Tent of Meeting to minister in
        the Holy Place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CYou shall take the ram of the ordination and boil its meat
        in a holy place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Aaron and his sons shall eat the meat of the ram and the bread in
        the basket, at the doorway of the Tent of Meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They shall eat those things by which atonement was made at their
        ordination and consecration; but a layman shall not eat them, because they
        are holy [that is, set apart to the worship of God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And if any of the meat of ordination or the bread remains until morning,
        you shall burn it in the fire; it shall not be eaten, because it is holy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CSo you shall do to Aaron and to his sons in accordance with
        all I have commanded you; during seven days you are to ordain them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "You shall offer a bull every day as a sin offering for atonement.
        You shall cleanse the altar from sin when you make atonement for it, and
        you shall anoint it to consecrate it [for God\u2019s sacred purpose]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For seven days you shall make atonement for the altar [of burnt offering]
        and consecrate it; then the altar shall be most holy. Whatever touches the
        altar must be holy (set apart for God\u2019s service).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "\u201CNow this is what you shall offer on the altar: two one year
        old lambs shall be offered each day, continuously. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'One lamb you shall offer in the morning and the other lamb at twilight; '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'and with the one lamb there shall be one-tenth of a measure of fine
        flour mixed with one-fourth of a hin of beaten [olive] oil, and one-fourth
        of a hin of wine for a drink offering [to be poured out]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And the other lamb you shall offer at twilight, and do with it as
        with the grain offering of the morning and with the drink offering, for a
        sweet and soothing aroma [to appease God], an offering by fire to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'This will be a continual burnt offering throughout your generations
        at the doorway of the Tent of Meeting before the Lord, where I will meet
        with you, to speak to you there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "There I will meet with the Israelites, and the Tent of Meeting shall
        be sanctified by My glory [the Shekinah, God\u2019s dwelling presence]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'I will sanctify the Tent of Meeting and the altar [of burnt offering];
        also I will sanctify Aaron and his sons to serve as priests to Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'I will dwell among the sons of Israel and be their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: They shall know [from personal experience] and acknowledge that I
        am the Lord their God who brought them out of the land of Egypt so that I
        might dwell among them; I am the Lord their God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Altar of Incense'
      title: The Altar of Incense
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CYou shall make an altar upon which to burn incense; you shall
        make it of acacia wood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It shall be a cubit long and a cubit wide. It shall be square and
        it shall be two cubits high. Its horns of one piece with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall overlay it with pure gold, its top and its sides all around,
        and its horns; and you shall make a gold molding all around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You shall make two gold rings under its molding, make them on the
        two side walls\u2014on opposite sides\u2014they shall be holders for the
        poles with which to carry it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall make the poles of acacia wood overlaid with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall put the altar of incense [in the Holy Place] in front and
        outside of the veil that screens the ark of the Testimony, before the mercy
        seat that is over the Testimony, where I will meet with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Aaron shall burn sweet and fragrant incense on it; he shall burn
        it every morning when he trims and tends the lamps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When Aaron sets up the lamps at twilight, he shall burn incense,
        a perpetual incense before the Lord throughout your generations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You shall not offer any strange incense on this altar, or burnt offering
        or meal offering; you shall not pour out a drink offering on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Ransom Money'
      title: The Ransom Money
      number: 10
      content: "Once a year Aaron shall make atonement [for sin] on its horns. He
        shall make atonement on it with the blood of the sin offering of atonement
        once a year throughout your generations. It is most holy to the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then the Lord said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CWhen you take the census of the Israelites, each one shall
        give a ransom for himself to the Lord when you count them, so that no plague
        will come on them when you number them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'This is what everyone who is counted shall give [as he joins those
        already counted]: a half shekel, according to the sanctuary shekel (the shekel
        is twenty gerahs); a half shekel as a contribution to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Everyone who is counted, from twenty years old and over, [as he joins
        those already counted], shall give this contribution to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The rich shall not give more and the poor shall not give less than
        half a shekel, when you give this contribution to the Lord to make atonement
        for yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Bronze Basin'
      title: The Bronze Basin
      number: 16
      content: "You shall take the atonement money from the Israelites and use it
        [exclusively] for the service of the Tent of Meeting, so that it may be a
        memorial for the Israelites before the Lord, to make atonement for yourselves.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the Lord said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall also make a basin of bronze, with a base of bronze,
        for washing. You shall put it [outside in the court] between the Tent of
        Meeting and the altar [of burnt offering], and you shall put water in it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When they enter the Tent of Meeting, they shall wash with water,
        so that they will not die. Also, when they approach the altar to minister,
        to burn an offering in the fire to the Lord [they shall do the same]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Anointing Oil'
      title: The Anointing Oil
      number: 21
      content: "They shall wash their hands and their feet, so that they will not
        die; it shall be a perpetual statute for them, for Aaron and his descendants
        throughout their generations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Moreover, the Lord said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CTake for yourself the best spices: five hundred shekels of
        liquid myrrh, half as much\u2014two hundred and fifty\u2014of sweet-scented
        cinnamon, and two hundred and fifty of fragrant cane, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and five hundred shekels of cinnamon blossom according to the sanctuary
        shekel, and a hin of olive oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'You shall make of these a holy anointing oil, a perfume mixture,
        the work of a perfumer; it shall be a sacred anointing oil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'You shall anoint the Tent of Meeting with it, and the ark of the
        Testimony, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and the table [for the bread] and all its utensils, and the lampstand
        and its utensils, and the altar of incense, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and the altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, and the basin
        [for cleansing] and its base. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You shall consecrate them, that they may be most holy; whatever touches
        them must be holy (set apart for God). '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'You shall anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that they
        may serve as priests to Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "You shall say to the Israelites, \u2018This shall be a holy and sacred
        anointing oil, to Me [alone] throughout your generations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "It shall not be poured on anyone\u2019s body, nor shall you make
        any like it in the same composition. It is holy, and it shall be sacred to
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: The Incense'
      title: The Incense
      number: 33
      content: "Whoever prepares any like it or puts any of it on a layman shall
        be cut off from his people [excluding him from the atonement made for them].\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CTake sweet and fragrant spices\u2014stacte,
        onycha, and galbanum, sweet and fragrant spices with pure frankincense; there
        shall be an equal amount of each\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'and make incense with it, a perfume, the work of a perfumer, salted,
        pure and sacred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'You shall crush some of it [into a] very fine [powder], and put some
        of it before the Testimony in the Tent of Meeting, where I will meet with
        you; it shall be most holy to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'The incense which you shall make, you shall not make in the same
        proportions for yourselves; it shall be holy to you for the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Whoever makes any like it, to use as perfume shall be cut off from
        his people [excluding him from the atonement made for them].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Skilled Craftsmen'
      title: The Skilled Craftsmen
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the Lord said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSee, I have called by name Bezalel, son of Uri, the son of
        Hur, of the tribe of Judah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I have filled him with the Spirit of God in wisdom and skill, in
        understanding and intelligence, in knowledge, and in all kinds of craftsmanship, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'to make artistic designs for work in gold, in silver, and in bronze, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and in the cutting of stones for settings, and in the carving of
        wood, to work in all kinds of craftsmanship. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And behold, I Myself have appointed with him Oholiab, son of Ahisamach,
        of the tribe of Dan; to all who are wise-hearted I have given the skill and
        ability to make everything that I have commanded you: '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "the Tent of Meeting, the ark of the Testimony, the mercy seat that
        is upon it, all the furnishings of the tent\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the table [for the bread] and its utensils, the pure gold lampstand
        with all its utensils, the [golden] altar of incense, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "the [bronze] altar of burnt offering with all its utensils, the basin
        and its base\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the finely worked garments, the holy garments for Aaron the [high]
        priest and the garments for his sons to minister as priests, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Sign of the Sabbath'
      title: The Sign of the Sabbath
      number: 11
      content: "and the anointing oil and the sweet and fragrant incense for the
        Holy Place. They are to make them according to all that I have commanded
        you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the Lord said to Moses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CBut as for you, say to the Israelites, \u2018You shall most
        certainly observe My Sabbaths, for it is a sign between Me and you throughout
        your generations, so that you may know [without any doubt] and acknowledge
        that I am the Lord who sanctifies you and sets you apart [for Myself]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore, you shall keep the Sabbath, for it is holy to you. Everyone
        who profanes it must be put to death; for whoever does work on the Sabbath,
        that person (soul) shall be cut off from among his people [excluding him
        from the atonement made for them]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For six days work may be done, but the seventh is the Sabbath of
        complete rest, sacred to the Lord; whoever does work on the Sabbath day must
        be put to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So the Israelites shall observe the Sabbath, to celebrate the Sabbath
        throughout their generations as a perpetual covenant.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "It is a sign between Me and the Israelites forever; for in six days
        the Lord made the heavens and the earth, and on the seventh day He ceased
        and was refreshed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: When He had finished speaking with him on Mount Sinai, He gave Moses
        the two tablets of the Testimony, tablets of stone, written with the finger
        of God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Golden Calf'
      title: The Golden Calf
      number: 1
      content: "  Now when the people saw that Moses delayed coming down from the
        mountain, they gathered together before Aaron and said to him, \u201CCome,
        make us a god who will go before us; as for this Moses, the man who brought
        us up from the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So Aaron replied to them, \u201CTake off the gold rings that are
        in the ears of your wives, your sons and daughters, and bring them to me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So all the people took off the gold rings that were in their ears
        and brought them to Aaron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he took the gold from their hands, and fashioned it with an engraving
        tool and made it into a molten calf; and they said, \u201CThis is your god,
        O Israel, who brought you up from the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now when Aaron saw the molten calf, he built an altar before it;
        and Aaron made a proclamation, and said, \u201CTomorrow shall be a feast
        to the Lord!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So they got up early the next day and offered burnt offerings, and
        brought peace offerings; then the people sat down to eat and drink, and got
        up to play [shamefully\u2014without moral restraint].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CGo down at once, for your people,
        whom you brought up from the land of Egypt, have corrupted themselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They have quickly turned aside from the way which I commanded them.
        They have made themselves a molten calf, and have worshiped it and sacrificed
        to it, and said, \u2018This is your god, O Israel, who brought you up from
        the land of Egypt!\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Lord said to Moses, \u201CI have seen this people, and behold,
        they are a stiff-necked (stubborn, rebellious) people. "
      comments: []
    - name: "10: Moses\u2019 Entreaty"
      title: "Moses\u2019 Entreaty"
      number: 10
      content: "Now therefore, let Me alone and do not interfere, so that My anger
        may burn against them and that I may destroy them; and I will make of you
        (your descendants) a great nation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Moses appeased and entreated the Lord his God, and said, \u201CLord,
        why does Your anger burn against Your people whom You have brought out of
        the land of Egypt with great power and a mighty hand? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Why should the Egyptians say, \u2018With evil [intent] their God
        brought them out to kill them in the mountains and destroy them from the
        face of the earth\u2019? Turn away from Your burning anger and change Your
        mind about harming Your people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel (Jacob), Your servants to whom
        You swore [an oath] by Yourself, and said to them, \u2018I will multiply
        your descendants as the stars of the heavens, and all this land of which
        I have spoken I will give to your descendants, and they shall inherit it
        forever.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the Lord changed His mind about the harm which He had said He
        would do to His people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Moses turned and went down from the mountain with the two tablets
        of the Testimony in his hand; tablets that were written on both sides\u2014they
        were written on one side and on the other. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The tablets were the work of God; the writing was the writing of
        God engraved on the tablets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now when Joshua heard the noise of the people as they shouted, he
        said to Moses, \u201CThere is a sound of battle in the camp.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "18: Moses\u2019 Anger"
      title: "Moses\u2019 Anger"
      number: 18
      content: "But Moses said,\u201CIt is not the sound of the cry of victory,Nor
        is it the sound of the cry of defeat;But I hear the sound of singing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And as soon as he approached the camp and he saw the calf and the
        dancing, Moses\u2019 anger burned; and he threw the tablets from his hands
        and smashed them at the foot of the mountain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then Moses took the calf they had made and burned it in the fire,
        and ground it to powder, and scattered it on the surface of the water and
        made the Israelites drink it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Moses said to Aaron, \u201CWhat did this people do to you, that
        you have brought so great a sin on them?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Aaron said, \u201CDo not let the anger of my lord burn; you know
        the people yourself, that they are prone to evil. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For they said to me, \u2018Make us a god who will go before us; as
        for this Moses, the man who brought us out of the land of Egypt, we do not
        know what has become of him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "I said to them, \u2018Let whoever has gold [jewelry], take it off.\u2019
        So they gave it to me; then I threw it into the fire, and out came this calf.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now when Moses saw that the people were out of control\u2014for Aaron
        had let them get out of control to the point of being an object of mockery
        among their enemies\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "then Moses stood in the gate of the camp, and said, \u201CWhoever
        is on the Lord\u2019s side, come to me!\u201D And all the sons of Levi [the
        priestly tribe] gathered together to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He said to them, \u201CThus says the Lord God of Israel, \u2018Every
        man strap his sword on his thigh and go back and forth from gate to gate
        throughout the camp, and every man kill his brother, and every man his friend,
        and every man his neighbor [all who continue pagan worship].\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So the sons of Levi did as Moses instructed, and about three thousand
        men of the people [of Israel] were killed that day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Then Moses said [to the Levites], \u201CDedicate yourselves today
        to the Lord\u2014for each man has been against his own son and his own brother
        [in his attempt to escape execution]\u2014so that He may restore and bestow
        His blessing on you this day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then the next day Moses said to the people, \u201CYou have committed
        a great sin. Now I will go up to the Lord; perhaps I can make atonement for
        your sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So Moses returned to the Lord, and said, \u201COh, these people have
        committed a great sin [against You], and have made themselves a god of gold. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Yet now, if You will, forgive their sin\u2014and if not, please blot
        me out of Your book which You have written (kill me)!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But the Lord said to Moses, \u201CWhoever has sinned against Me,
        I will blot him out of My book [not you]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But now go, lead the people [to the place] where I have told you.
        Behold, My Angel shall go before you; nevertheless, in the day when I punish,
        I will punish them for their sin!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: So the Lord struck the people with a plague, because of what they
        had done with the calf which Aaron had made [for them].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Journey Resumed'
      title: The Journey Resumed
      number: 1
      content: "  The Lord spoke to Moses, saying, \u201CDepart, go up from here,
        you and the people whom you have brought from the land of Egypt, to the land
        which I swore to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob (Israel), saying, \u2018To your
        descendants I will give it.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will send an Angel before you and I will drive out the Canaanite,
        the Amorite, the Hittite, the Perizzite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Go up to a land [of abundance] flowing with milk and honey; for I
        will not go up in your midst, because you are a stiff-necked (stubborn, rebellious)
        people, and I might destroy you on the way.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the people heard this sad word, they mourned, and none of them
        put on his ornaments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For the Lord had said to Moses, \u201CSay to the sons of Israel,
        \u2018You are a stiff-necked (stubborn, rebellious) people! If I should come
        among you for one moment, I would destroy you. Now therefore, [penitently]
        take off your ornaments, so that I may know what to do with you.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the Israelites left off all their ornaments [in repentance], from
        Mount Horeb (Sinai) onward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now Moses used to take his own tent and pitch it outside the camp,
        far away from the camp, and he called it the tent of meeting [of God with
        His own people]. And everyone who sought the Lord would go out to the [temporary]
        tent of meeting which was outside the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Whenever Moses went out to the tent, all the people would rise and
        stand, each at his tent door, and look at Moses until he entered the tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Whenever Moses entered the tent, the pillar of cloud would descend
        and stand at the doorway of the tent; and the Lord would speak with Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When all the people saw the pillar of cloud standing at the tent
        door, all the people would rise and worship, each at his tent door. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Moses Intercedes'
      title: Moses Intercedes
      number: 11
      content: 'And so the Lord used to speak to Moses face to face, just as a man
        speaks to his friend. When Moses returned to the camp, his attendant Joshua,
        the son of Nun, a young man, would not depart from the tent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Moses said to the Lord, \u201CSee, You say to me, \u2018Bring up
        this people,\u2019 but You have not let me know whom You will send with me.
        Yet You have said, \u2018I know you by name, and you have also found favor
        in My sight.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now therefore, I pray you, if I have found favor in Your sight, let
        me know Your ways so that I may know You [becoming more deeply and intimately
        acquainted with You, recognizing and understanding Your ways more clearly]
        and that I may find grace and favor in Your sight. And consider also, that
        this nation is Your people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CMy presence shall go with you, and I will
        give you rest [by bringing you and the people into the promised land].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Moses said to Him, \u201CIf Your presence does not go [with me],
        do not lead us up from here. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For how then can it be known that Your people and I have found favor
        in Your sight? Is it not by Your going with us, so that we are distinguished,
        Your people and I, from all the [other] people on the face of the earth?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The Lord said to Moses, \u201CI will also do this thing that you
        have asked; for you have found favor (lovingkindness, mercy) in My sight
        and I have known you [personally] by name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Moses said, \u201CPlease, show me Your glory!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And God said, \u201CI will make all My goodness pass before you,
        and I will proclaim the Name of the Lord before you; for I will be gracious
        to whom I will be gracious, and will show compassion (lovingkindness) on
        whom I will show compassion.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But He said, \u201CYou cannot see My face, for no man shall see Me
        and live!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the Lord said, \u201CBehold, there is a place beside Me, and
        you shall stand there on the rock; "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and while My glory is passing by, I will put you in a cleft of the
        rock and protectively cover you with My hand until I have passed by. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then I will take away My hand and you shall see My back; but My face
        shall not be seen.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Two Tablets Replaced'
      title: The Two Tablets Replaced
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CCut two tablets of stone like
        the first, and I will write on these tablets the words that were on the first
        tablets which you smashed [when you learned of Israel\u2019s idolatry]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So be ready by morning, and come up in the morning to Mount Sinai,
        and present yourself there to Me on the top of the mountain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "No man is to come up with you, nor let any man be seen anywhere on
        the mountain; nor let flocks or herds feed in front of that mountain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Moses cut two tablets of stone like the first ones, and he got
        up early in the morning and went up on Mount Sinai, as the Lord had commanded
        him, and took the two tablets of stone in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the Lord descended in the cloud and stood there with Moses as
        he proclaimed the Name of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the Lord passed by in front of him, and proclaimed, \u201CThe
        Lord, the Lord God, compassionate and gracious, slow to anger, and abounding
        in lovingkindness and truth (faithfulness); "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "keeping mercy and lovingkindness for thousands, forgiving iniquity
        and transgression and sin; but He will by no means leave the guilty unpunished,
        visiting (avenging) the iniquity (sin, guilt) of the fathers upon the children
        and the grandchildren to the third and fourth generations [that is, calling
        the children to account for the sins of their fathers].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Moses bowed to the earth immediately and worshiped [the Lord]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Covenant Renewed'
      title: The Covenant Renewed
      number: 9
      content: "And he said, \u201CIf now I have found favor and lovingkindness in
        Your sight, O Lord, let the Lord, please, go in our midst, though it is a
        stiff-necked (stubborn, rebellious) people, and pardon our iniquity and our
        sin, and take us as Your possession.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then God said, \u201CBehold, I am going to make a covenant. Before
        all your people I will do wondrous works (miracles) such as have not been
        created or produced in all the earth nor among any of the nations; and all
        the people among whom you live shall see the working of the Lord, for it
        is a fearful and awesome thing that I am going to do with you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CBe sure to observe what I am commanding you this day: behold,
        I am going to drive out the Amorite before you, and the Canaanite, the Hittite,
        the Perizzite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Watch yourself so that you do not make a covenant (solemn agreement,
        treaty) with the inhabitants of the land into which you are going, or it
        will become a [dangerous] trap among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But you shall tear down and destroy their [pagan] altars, smash in
        pieces their [sacred] pillars (obelisks, images) and cut down their Asherim '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u2014for you shall not worship any other god; for the Lord, whose
        name is Jealous, is a jealous (impassioned) God [demanding what is rightfully
        and uniquely His]\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'otherwise you might make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land
        and they would play the prostitute with their gods and sacrifice to their
        gods, and someone might invite you to eat his sacrifice (meal), '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and you might take some of his daughters for your sons, and his daughters
        would play the prostitute with their gods and cause your sons also to play
        the prostitute (commit apostasy) with their gods [that is, abandon the true
        God for man-made idols]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You shall make for yourselves no molten gods.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CYou shall observe the Feast of Unleavened Bread (Passover).
        For seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, as I have commanded you, at
        the appointed time in the month of Abib; for in the month of Abib you came
        out of Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CAll the firstborn males among your livestock belong to Me,
        whether cattle or sheep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You shall redeem the firstborn of a donkey with a lamb; but if you
        do not redeem it, then you shall break its neck. You shall redeem all the
        firstborn of your sons. None of you are to appear before Me empty-handed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CYou shall work for six days, but on the seventh day you shall
        rest; [even] in plowing time and in harvest you shall rest [on the Sabbath]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "You shall observe and celebrate the Feast of Weeks (Harvest, First
        Fruits, or Pentecost), the first fruits of the wheat harvest, and the Feast
        of Ingathering (Booths or Tabernacles) at the year\u2019s end. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Three times a year all your males shall appear before the Lord God,
        the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For I will drive out and dispossess nations before you and enlarge
        your borders; nor shall any man covet (actively seek for himself) your land
        when you go up to appear before the Lord your God three times a year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CYou shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leavened
        bread, nor shall the sacrifice of the Feast of the Passover (Unleavened Bread)
        be left over until morning.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CYou shall bring the very first of the first fruits of your
        ground to the house of the Lord your God.\u201CYou shall not boil a young
        goat in his mother\u2019s milk [as some pagans do].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the Lord said to Moses, \u201CWrite these words, for in accordance
        with these words I have made a covenant with you and with Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Moses\u2019 Face Shines"
      title: "Moses\u2019 Face Shines"
      number: 28
      content: 'Moses was there with the Lord forty days and forty nights; he ate
        no bread and drank no water. And he wrote on the tablets the words of the
        covenant, the Ten Commandments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'When Moses came down from Mount Sinai with the two tablets of the
        Testimony in his hand, he did not know that the skin of his face was shining
        [with a unique radiance] because he had been speaking with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When Aaron and all the Israelites saw Moses, behold, the skin of
        his face shone, and they were afraid to approach him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But Moses called to them, and Aaron and all the leaders of the congregation
        returned to him; and he spoke to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Afterward all the Israelites approached him, and he commanded them
        to do everything that the Lord had said to him on Mount Sinai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'When Moses had finished speaking with them, he put a veil over his
        face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But whenever Moses went in before the Lord to speak with Him, he
        would take off the veil until he came out. When he came out and he told the
        Israelites what he had been commanded [by God], '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: the Israelites would see the face of Moses, how his skin shone [with
        a unique radiance]. So Moses put the veil on his face again until he went
        in to speak with God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sabbath Emphasized'
      title: The Sabbath Emphasized
      number: 1
      content: "  Moses gathered all the congregation of the sons of Israel together,
        and said to them, \u201CThese are the things which the Lord has commanded
        you to do:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CFor six days work may be done, but the seventh day shall be
        a holy day for you, a Sabbath of complete rest to the Lord; whoever does
        any kind of work on that day shall be put to death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You shall not kindle a fire in any of your dwellings on the Sabbath
        day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Moses said to all the congregation of the sons of Israel, \u201CThis
        is the thing which the Lord has commanded: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018Take from among you an offering to the Lord. Whoever has a
        willing heart, let him bring it as the Lord\u2019s offering: gold, silver,
        and bronze, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "blue, purple, and scarlet fabric, fine linen, goats\u2019 hair,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and rams\u2019 skins dyed red, and skins of porpoises, and acacia
        wood, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and [olive] oil for the lighting, and balsam for the anointing oil,
        and for the fragrant incense, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Tabernacle Workmen'
      title: Tabernacle Workmen
      number: 9
      content: 'and onyx stones and other stones to be set for the ephod and the
        breastpiece.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u2018Let every skilled and talented man among you come, and make
        everything that the Lord has commanded: "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the tabernacle (sacred dwelling of God), its tent and its covering,
        its hooks, its boards, its bars, its pillars, and its sockets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the ark [of the covenant] and its carrying poles, with the mercy
        seat and the veil (partition curtain) of the screen [to hang between the
        Holy Place and the Holy of Holies]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the table and its carrying poles, and all its utensils, and the bread
        of the [divine] Presence (showbread); '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the lampstand also for the light and its utensils and its lamps,
        and the oil for the light; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and the altar of incense and its carrying poles, the anointing oil
        and the fragrant incense, the screen (curtain) for the doorway at the entrance
        of the tabernacle; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the altar of burnt offering with its bronze grating, its carrying
        poles, and all its utensils, the wash basin and its base (stand); '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "the court\u2019s curtains, its support poles and their sockets, and
        the curtain for the gate of the courtyard; "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the pegs of the tabernacle and the pegs of the court and their cords; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Gifts Received'
      title: Gifts Received
      number: 19
      content: "the finely-woven garments for ministering in the Holy Place, the
        holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments for his sons, to minister
        as priests.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then all the congregation of the Israelites left Moses\u2019 presence. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Everyone whose heart stirred him and everyone whose spirit moved
        him came and brought the Lord\u2019s offering to be used for the Tent of
        Meeting, for all its service, and for the holy garments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then all whose hearts moved them, both men and women, came and brought
        brooches, earrings or nose rings, signet rings, and necklaces, all jewels
        of gold; everyone bringing an offering of gold to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Every man who had in his possession blue or purple or scarlet fabric,
        and fine linen, and goats\u2019 hair, and rams\u2019 skins dyed red and porpoise
        skins, brought them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Everyone who could make an offering of silver or bronze brought it
        as the Lord\u2019s offering; every man who had in his possession acacia wood
        for any work of the service brought it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'All the skilled and talented women spun thread with their hands,
        and brought what they had spun, blue and purple and scarlet fabric and fine
        linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "All the women whose heart stirred with a skill spun the goats\u2019
        hair.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The leaders brought onyx stones and other stones to be put in settings
        for the ephod and for the breastpiece, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and spice and [olive] oil for the light and for the anointing oil
        and for the fragrant incense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The Israelites, all the men and women whose heart moved them to bring
        material for all the work which the Lord had commanded through Moses to be
        done, brought a freewill (voluntary) offering to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Moses said to the Israelites, \u201CSee, the Lord called by
        name Bezalel son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah; "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and He has filled him with the Spirit of God, with wisdom and skill,
        with intelligence and understanding, and with knowledge in all [areas of]
        craftsmanship, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'to devise artistic designs to work in gold, silver, and bronze, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'and in the cutting of stones for setting and in the carving of wood,
        for work in every skilled craft. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "He has also put in Bezalel\u2019s heart [the willingness] to teach
        [others the same skills], both he and Oholiab, son of Ahisamach, of the tribe
        of Dan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: He has filled them with skill to do the work of an engraver, of a
        designer, and of an embroiderer, in blue, purple, and scarlet fabric, and
        in fine linen, and of a weaver; makers of every work and embroiderers of
        [excellent] designs.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tabernacle Underwritten'
      title: The Tabernacle Underwritten
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBezalel and Oholiab, and every skilled person in whom the
        Lord has put ability and understanding to know how to do all the work in
        the construction of the sanctuary, shall work according to all that the Lord
        has commanded.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Moses called Bezalel and Oholiab and every skilled person in whom
        the Lord had put ability, everyone whose heart stirred him, to come to do
        the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They received from Moses all the offerings which the Israelites had
        brought for the construction of the sanctuary, to prepare it for service.
        And they continued to bring him freewill (voluntary) offerings every morning. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And all the skilled men who were doing all the work on the sanctuary
        came, each one from the work which he was doing, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and they said to Moses, \u201CThe people are bringing much more than
        enough for the construction work which the Lord commanded us to do.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Moses issued a command, and it was proclaimed throughout the camp,
        \u201CLet neither man nor woman do any more work for the sanctuary offering.\u201D
        So the people were restrained from bringing anything more;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Construction Proceeds'
      title: Construction Proceeds
      number: 7
      content: 'for the material they had was sufficient and more than enough to
        do all the work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All the skilled men among them who were doing the work on the tabernacle
        made ten curtains of fine twisted linen and blue, purple, and scarlet fabric,
        with cherubim [worked into them], the work of an embroiderer, Bezalel made
        them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Each curtain was twenty-eight cubits long and four cubits wide; all
        the curtains were one size. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Bezalel joined five curtains one to another, and [the other] five
        curtains he joined one to another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He made loops of blue on the edge of the outermost curtain in the
        first set; he also did this on the edge of the curtain that was outermost
        in the second set. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He made fifty loops in the one curtain [of the first set] and fifty
        loops on the edge of the curtain which was in the second set; the loops were
        opposite one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He made fifty gold hooks and joined the curtains together with the
        hooks, so that the tabernacle became a unit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he made curtains of goats\u2019 hair for a tent over the tabernacle;
        he made eleven curtains in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Each curtain was thirty cubits long and four cubits wide; the eleven
        curtains were of equal size. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Bezalel joined five curtains by themselves and [the other] six curtains
        by themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He made fifty loops on the edge of the outermost curtain in the first
        set, and he made fifty loops on the edge of the outermost curtain of the
        second set. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He made fifty bronze hooks to join the tent together into a unit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "He made a [third] covering for the tent of rams\u2019 skins dyed
        red, and above it a [fourth] covering of porpoise skins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Bezalel made boards of acacia wood for the upright framework of the
        tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Each board was ten cubits long and one and a half cubits wide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Each board had two tenons (dovetails), fitted to one another; he
        did this for all the boards of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And [this is how] he made the boards [for frames] for the tabernacle:
        twenty boards for the south side; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and he made under the twenty boards forty silver sockets; two sockets
        under one board for its two tenons (dovetails), and two sockets under another
        board for its two tenons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'For the other side of the tabernacle, the north side, he made twenty
        boards, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and their forty silver sockets; two sockets under [the end of] each
        board. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And for the rear of the tabernacle, to the west, he made six [frame]
        boards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he made two boards for each corner of the tabernacle in the rear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'They were separate below, but linked together at the top with one
        ring; thus he made both of them in both corners. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'There were eight boards with sixteen silver sockets, and under [the
        end of] each board two sockets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Bezalel made bars of acacia wood, five for the [frame] boards of
        the one side of the tabernacle, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and five bars for the boards of the tabernacle\u2019s other side,
        and five bars for the boards at the rear side to the west. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And he made the middle bar pass through [horizontally] halfway up
        the boards from one end to the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'He overlaid the boards and the bars with gold and made their rings
        of gold as holders for the bars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Further, Bezalel made the veil of blue and purple and scarlet fabric,
        and fine twisted linen; he made it with cherubim, the work of an embroiderer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For the veil (partition curtain) he made four support poles of acacia
        wood and overlaid them with gold; their hooks were gold, and he cast for
        them four silver sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'He made a screen (curtain) for the doorway of the tent, of blue,
        purple, and scarlet fabric, and fine twisted linen, the work of an embroiderer; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: and [he made] the five support poles with their hooks, and overlaid
        their [ornamental] tops and connecting rings with gold; but their five sockets
        were bronze.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Construction Continues'
      title: Construction Continues
      number: 1
      content: "  Bezalel made the ark [of the covenant] of acacia wood\u2014it was
        two and a half cubits long, and one and a half cubits wide, and one and a
        half cubits high. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he overlaid it with pure gold inside and out, and made a molding
        (border) of gold to go all around [the top of it]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He cast four rings of gold for it on its four feet, two rings on
        one side and two rings on the other side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He made carrying poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He put the carrying poles through the rings at the sides of the ark,
        to carry it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Bezalel made the mercy seat of pure gold; it was two and a half cubits
        long, and one and a half cubits wide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He made two cherubim of hammered gold; he made them at the two ends
        of the mercy seat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'one cherub at one end and one cherub at the other end; he made the
        cherubim [of one piece] with the mercy seat at the two ends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The cherubim spread out their wings upward, covering and protecting
        the mercy seat with their wings, with their faces toward each other; the
        faces of the cherubim were [looking downward] toward the mercy seat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Bezalel made the table [for the bread] of acacia wood; it was two
        cubits long, a cubit wide, and one and a half cubits high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He overlaid it with pure gold, and made a border of gold for it all
        around [its top]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He made a rim for it [just under the top] a hand width wide all around,
        and a border of gold around its rim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He cast four rings of gold for it and fastened the rings to the four
        corners that were at its four legs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Close by the rim were the rings, the holders for the poles [to pass
        through] to carry the table. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Bezalel made the carrying poles of acacia wood to carry the table
        and overlaid them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He made the utensils which were to be on the table, its dishes and
        its pans [for bread], its bowls and its jars for pouring drink offerings,
        of pure gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then he made the lampstand (menorah) of pure gold. He made the lampstand
        of hammered work, its base and its [center] shaft; its cups, its calyxes,
        and its flowers were all of one piece with it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There were six branches coming out of the sides of the lampstand,
        three branches from one side of the center shaft and three branches from
        the other side of it; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "three cups shaped like almond blossoms, a calyx and a flower in one
        branch, and three cups shaped like almond blossoms, a calyx and a flower
        in the opposite branch\u2014so for the six branches coming out of the center
        shaft of the lampstand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'On the center shaft of the lampstand there were four cups shaped
        like almond blossoms, with calyxes and flowers [one at the top]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and a calyx was under the first pair of branches coming out of it,
        and a calyx under the second pair of branches, coming out of it, and a calyx
        under the third pair of branches coming out of it, for the six branches coming
        out of the lampstand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Their calyxes and their branches were of one piece with it; all of
        it was a single hammered work of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He made its seven lamps with its snuffers and its trays of pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He made the lampstand and all its utensils from a talent of pure
        gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Bezalel made the incense altar of acacia wood; its top was a
        cubit square and it was two cubits high; the horns were of one piece with
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He overlaid it with pure gold, its top, its sides all around and
        its horns; he also made a rim of gold around it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He made two rings of gold for it under its rim, on its two opposite
        sides, as holders for the poles [to pass through] to carry it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: He also made the holy anointing oil and the pure, fragrant incense
        of spices, the work of a perfumer.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tabernacle Completed'
      title: The Tabernacle Completed
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Bezalel made the altar of burnt offering of acacia wood; its
        top was square, five cubits long and five cubits wide, and three cubits high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he made its horns (horn-shaped projections) on the four corners
        of it; the horns were of one piece with it, and he overlaid it with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He made all the utensils and vessels of the altar [of burnt offering],
        the pots, shovels, basins [to catch the blood of the sacrificed animal],
        meat hooks and the firepans [to store live coals]. He made all its utensils
        of bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He made for the altar a grating of bronze mesh under its rim, extending
        halfway up it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He cast four rings for the four corners of the bronze grating as
        holders for the carrying poles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he made the carrying poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with
        bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He put the poles through the rings on the sides of the altar, with
        which to carry it; he made it hollow with planks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Bezalel made the basin and its base of bronze from the mirrors of
        the attending women who served and ministered at the doorway of the Tent
        of Meeting.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then he made the court: for the south side the curtains of the court
        were of fine twisted linen, a hundred cubits; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'their twenty support poles, and their twenty bronze sockets; the
        hooks of the support poles and their connecting rings were silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And for the north side [of the court the curtains were also] a hundred
        cubits; their twenty support poles and their twenty bronze sockets; the hooks
        of the support poles and their connecting rings were silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the west side [of the court] there were curtains of fifty cubits
        with their ten support poles and their ten sockets; the hooks of the support
        poles and their connecting rings were silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the east side [the front of the courtyard, there were curtains
        of] fifty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The curtains for one side of the court gate were fifteen cubits,
        with their three support poles and their three sockets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and the same for the other side [of the court gate]. Left and right
        of the court gate there were curtains of fifteen cubits; with their three
        support poles and their three sockets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'All the curtains around the court were of fine twisted linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The sockets for the support poles were made of bronze, the hooks
        of the support poles and their connecting rings were made of silver; and
        silver overlaid their tops. All the support poles of the court had silver
        connecting rings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The screen (curtain) for the gate of the courtyard [on the east side]
        was the work of an embroiderer, in blue, purple, and scarlet fabric, and
        fine twisted linen; it was twenty cubits long and five cubits high, corresponding
        to the curtains of the court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Their four support poles and their four sockets were bronze; their
        hooks were silver, and silver overlaid their tops and their connecting rings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: The Cost of the Tabernacle'
      title: The Cost of the Tabernacle
      number: 20
      content: 'All the pegs for the tabernacle and the court were bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'This is the sum of the things for the tabernacle, the tabernacle
        of the Testimony, as counted according to the command of Moses, for the work
        of the Levites, under the direction of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah,
        made everything that the Lord commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'With him was Oholiab the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan, an
        engraver and a skillful craftsman and an embroiderer in blue and in purple
        and in scarlet fabric, and in fine linen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'All the gold that was used for the work, in all the building and
        furnishing of the sanctuary, the gold from the wave offering, was twenty-nine
        talents and seven hundred and thirty shekels, according to the shekel of
        the sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The silver from those of the congregation who were assembled and
        counted was 100 talents and 1,775 shekels, according to the shekel of the
        sanctuary; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'a beka for each man (that is, half a shekel according to the shekel
        of the sanctuary) for everyone who was counted, from twenty years old and
        upward, for 603,550 men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The hundred talents of silver were for casting the sockets of the
        sanctuary and the sockets of the veil (partition curtain); a hundred sockets
        for the hundred talents, a talent for a socket. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Of the 1,775 shekels, he made hooks for the support poles and overlaid
        their tops and made connecting rings for them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The bronze of the wave offering was seventy talents and 2,400 shekels. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'With it Bezalel made the sockets for the doorway of the Tent of Meeting,
        and the bronze altar and its bronze grating, and all the utensils of the
        altar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: and the sockets of the court all around and the sockets of the court
        gate, and all the pegs of the tabernacle and all the pegs around the court.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Priestly Garments'
      title: The Priestly Garments
      number: 1
      content: '  Moreover, from the blue and purple and scarlet fabric, they made
        finely woven garments for serving and ministering in the Holy Place; they
        made the holy garments for Aaron, just as the Lord had commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Bezalel made the ephod of gold, and of blue, purple, and scarlet
        fabric, and fine twisted linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Bezalel and Oholiab hammered the gold [into thin sheets] and
        cut it into threads to work into the blue, purple, and scarlet fabric, and
        into the fine linen, the work of a skilled craftsman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They made attaching shoulder pieces for the ephod; it was attached
        at its two [upper] edges. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The skillfully woven sash with which to bind it, which was on the
        ephod [to hold it in place], was like its workmanship, of the same material:
        of gold and of blue, purple, and scarlet fabric, and fine twisted linen,
        just as the Lord had commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They made the onyx stones, set in settings of gold filigree; they
        were engraved as signets are engraved, with the names of [the twelve tribes
        of] the sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he put them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod to be memorial
        stones (a remembrance) for the sons of Israel (Jacob), just as the Lord had
        commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Bezalel made the breastpiece, the work of a skillful craftsman, like
        the workmanship of the ephod: of gold and of blue, purple, and scarlet fabric,
        and fine twisted linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "It was square; they made the breastpiece folded double, a [hand\u2019s]
        span long and a [hand\u2019s] span wide when folded double. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And they mounted four rows of stones on it. The first row was a row
        of ruby, topaz, and emerald; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and the second row, a turquoise, a sapphire, and a diamond; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and the third row, a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper; they were mounted
        in settings of gold filigree. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The stones corresponded to the names of the sons of Israel; they
        were twelve [in all], corresponding to their names, engraved like a signet,
        each with its name, for the twelve tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they made on the breastpiece twisted chains like cords of pure
        gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They made two settings of gold filigree and two gold rings, and put
        the two rings on the two ends of the breastpiece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then they put the two twisted cords of gold in the two rings on the
        ends of the breastpiece. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They put the [other] two ends of the two cords on the two filigree
        settings, and put them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod at the front of
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They made two rings of gold and put them on the two ends of the breastpiece,
        on its inner edge which was next to the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Furthermore, they made two [other] gold rings and attached them to
        the bottom of the two shoulder pieces of the ephod, at the front of it, close
        to the place where it is joined, above the woven sash of the ephod. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They bound the breastpiece by its rings to the rings of the ephod
        with a blue cord, so that it would lie on the woven sash of the ephod, and
        so that the breastpiece would not come loose from the ephod, just as the
        Lord commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Bezalel made the robe of the ephod of woven work, all of blue; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'there was an opening [for the head] in the middle of the robe, like
        the opening in a coat of armor, with a hem around it, so that it would not
        be frayed or torn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'On the hem of the robe they made pomegranates of blue, purple, and
        scarlet fabric, and fine twisted linen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'They also made bells of pure gold, and put the bells between the
        pomegranates around the hem of the robe; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'a bell and a pomegranate, a bell and a pomegranate, all [the way]
        around the hem of the robe, for service and ministering, just as the Lord
        commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And they made tunics of finely woven linen for Aaron and his sons, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and the turban of fine linen, and the ornamental caps of fine linen,
        and the linen undergarments of fine twisted linen, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and the sash of fine twisted linen, and blue, purple, and scarlet
        fabric, the work of an embroiderer, just as the Lord commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "They made the plate of the holy crown of pure gold, and wrote on
        it an inscription, like the engravings of a signet, \u201CHoly to the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'They tied a blue cord to it, to fasten it on the turban above, just
        as the Lord commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Thus all the work of the tabernacle of the Tent of Meeting was finished;
        and the Israelites did according to all that the Lord had commanded Moses;
        that is what they did. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'They brought the tabernacle to Moses [for him to inspect]: the tent
        and all its furnishings, its hooks, its [frame] boards, its bars, its support
        poles, its sockets or bases; '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "and the covering of rams\u2019 skins dyed red, and the covering of
        porpoise skins, and the veil (partition) of the screen (curtain); "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'the ark of the Testimony, its carrying poles and the mercy seat; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'the table and all its utensils and the bread of the Presence (showbread); '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'the pure gold lampstand and its lamps, with the lamps placed in order,
        all its utensils, and the oil for the light; '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'the golden altar [of incense], the anointing oil and the fragrant
        incense, and the [hanging] veil for the doorway of the tent; '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'the bronze altar [of burnt offering] and its grating of bronze, its
        poles and all its utensils, the basin and its base; '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'the curtains of the courtyard, its support poles and sockets, and
        the screen (curtain) for the courtyard gate, its cords and pegs, and all
        the utensils for the service of the tabernacle, for the Tent of Meeting [of
        God with His people]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'the [finely] woven garments for serving and ministering in the Holy
        Place, the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and the garments of his sons
        to minister as priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So the Israelites did all the work according to all that the Lord
        had commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: And Moses [carefully] inspected all the work, and behold, they had
        done it; just as the Lord had commanded, so had they done it. So Moses blessed
        them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Tabernacle Erected'
      title: The Tabernacle Erected
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the Lord spoke to Moses, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201COn the first day of the first month (Abib) you shall set up
        the tabernacle of the Tent of Meeting [of God with you]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You shall place the ark of the Testimony there, and you shall screen
        off the ark [from the Holy Place of God\u2019s Presence] with the veil (partition
        curtain). "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You shall bring in the table [for the bread] and arrange its setting;
        you shall bring in the lampstand and mount and light its lamps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You shall set the golden altar of incense in front of the ark of
        the Testimony [outside the veil], and put the [hanging] veil at the doorway
        of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall set the [bronze] altar of burnt offering in front of the
        doorway of the tabernacle of the Tent of Meeting. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You shall set the basin between the Tent of Meeting and the altar
        [of burnt offering], and put water in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You shall set up the courtyard [curtains] all around and hang up
        the screen (curtain) for the gateway of the courtyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then you shall take the anointing oil and anoint the tabernacle and
        all that is in it, and consecrate it and all its furniture; and it shall
        be holy (declared sacred, separated from secular use). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'You shall anoint the altar of burnt offering and all its utensils,
        and consecrate the altar, and the altar shall be most holy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You shall anoint the basin and its base, and consecrate it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then you shall bring Aaron and his sons to the doorway of the Tent
        of Meeting and wash them with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You shall put the holy garments on Aaron and anoint him and consecrate
        him, that he may serve as a priest to Me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall bring his sons and put tunics on them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "you shall anoint them just as you anointed their father, so that
        they may serve as priests to Me; and their anointing shall qualify them for
        an everlasting priesthood throughout their generations.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Thus Moses did; in accordance with all that the Lord commanded him,
        so he did.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now it happened on the first day of the first month (Abib) in the
        second year [after the exodus from Egypt], that the tabernacle was erected. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Moses erected the tabernacle, laid its sockets, set up its boards,
        put in its bars and erected its support poles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He spread the tent over the tabernacle and put the covering of the
        tent over it, just as the Lord had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He took the Testimony [the stones inscribed with the Ten Commandments]
        and put it into the ark [of the covenant], and placed the poles [through
        the rings] on the ark, and put the mercy seat on top of the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Moses brought the ark into the tabernacle, and set up a veil (partition)
        for the screen (curtain), and screened off the ark of the Testimony, just
        as the Lord had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then he put the table in the Tent of Meeting on the north side of
        the tabernacle, outside the veil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He set the bread [of the Presence] in order on it before the Lord,
        just as the Lord had commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then he put the lampstand in the Tent of Meeting, opposite the table,
        on the south side of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Moses mounted and lighted the lamps [on the lampstand] before the
        Lord, just as the Lord commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He put the golden altar [of incense] in the Tent of Meeting in front
        of the veil; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'he burned fragrant incense [as a symbol of prayer] on it, just as
        the Lord commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then he set up the screen (curtain) at the doorway of the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He set the altar of burnt offering before the doorway of the tabernacle
        of the Tent of Meeting, and offered on it the burnt offering and the grain
        offering, just as the Lord commanded him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'He placed the basin between the Tent of Meeting and the altar [of
        burnt offering], and put water in it for washing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then from it Moses and Aaron and his sons washed their hands and
        their feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When they entered the Tent of Meeting, and when they approached the
        altar, they washed, just as the Lord commanded Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: The Glory of the Lord'
      title: The Glory of the Lord
      number: 33
      content: 'And he erected the courtyard all around the tabernacle and the altar,
        and hung the screen (curtain) at the gateway of the courtyard. So Moses finished
        the work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then the cloud [the Shekinah, God\u2019s visible, dwelling presence]
        covered the Tent of Meeting, and the glory and brilliance of the Lord filled
        the tabernacle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Moses was not able to enter the Tent of Meeting because the cloud
        remained on it, and the glory and brilliance of the Lord filled the tabernacle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'In all their journeys, whenever the cloud was taken up from over
        the tabernacle, the Israelites would set out; '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'but if the cloud was not taken up, then they did not journey on until
        the day when it was taken up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: For throughout all their journeys, the cloud of the Lord was on the
        tabernacle by day, and there was fire in it by night, in the sight of all
        the house of Israel.
      comments: []
